{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01MSPMN88JjsR7LDVri1Pwyn","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.provider;\n     2→\n     3→import com.github.slugify.Slugify;\n     4→import jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\n     5→import lombok.AllArgsConstructor;\n     6→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.provider.SlugProvider;\n     7→\n     8→@ApplicationScoped\n     9→@AllArgsConstructor\n    10→public class SlugifySlugProvider implements SlugProvider {\n    11→\n    12→  private final Slugify slugify;\n    13→\n    14→  @Override\n    15→  public String slugify(String text) {\n    16→    return slugify.slugify(text);\n    17→  }\n    18→}\n    19→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01TazgD3f7VBwqVnJHcGjuo7","session_id":"4d21e41c-7b8c-412a-ac18-df8336bdf9ca","uuid":"ddff3fa4-5a57-41f2-ba01-af1a61973a46"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01DvF56KdbTYqepGcGo2iF2p","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.provider;\n     2→\n     3→import io.smallrye.jwt.build.Jwt;\n     4→import jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\n     5→import java.util.*;\n     6→\n     7→@ApplicationScoped\n     8→public class JwtTokenProvider {\n     9→\n    10→  public String createUserToken(String subject) {\n    11→    return Jwt.issuer(\"users-service\")\n    12→        .subject(subject)\n    13→        .groups(new HashSet<>(List.of(\"USER\")))\n    14→        .sign();\n    15→  }\n    16→}\n    17→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01TazgD3f7VBwqVnJHcGjuo7","session_id":"4d21e41c-7b8c-412a-ac18-df8336bdf9ca","uuid":"ea79ba23-4aed-4070-9fae-1e948c4270de"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_013L1qh9WkfUfdvk7nEMoXqC","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.provider;\n     2→\n     3→import io.quarkus.elytron.security.common.BcryptUtil;\n     4→import jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\n     5→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.provider.HashProvider;\n     6→\n     7→@ApplicationScoped\n     8→public class BCryptHashProvider implements HashProvider {\n     9→\n    10→  @Override\n    11→  public String hashPassword(String password) {\n    12→    return BcryptUtil.bcryptHash(password);\n    13→  }\n    14→\n    15→  @Override\n    16→  public boolean checkPassword(String plaintext, String hashed) {\n    17→    return BcryptUtil.matches(plaintext, hashed);\n    18→  }\n    19→}\n    20→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01TazgD3f7VBwqVnJHcGjuo7","session_id":"4d21e41c-7b8c-412a-ac18-df8336bdf9ca","uuid":"b09b5fc0-17c1-49d2-854c-a705e7669fc4"}
