{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01QU2eALwbsBythcUmYfU2Je","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"CDI issue: `EntityUtils` has `@ApplicationScoped` and `@AllArgsConstructor` but the beans it depends on (like `UserModelBuilder`) are not CDI managed beans - they're produced by configuration classes. The issue is that `EntityUtils` uses constructor injection via Lombok's `@AllArgsConstructor`, but `beans.xml` is set to `bean-discovery-mode=\"annotated\"`. The `EntityUtils` class has `@ApplicationScoped` and `@AllArgsConstructor`, and its constructor parameters (builders) are provided by the `@Produces` methods in configuration classes.\n\nThe real issue is more fundamental: the beans.xml discovery mode. Let me change it to `all` to discover all beans:"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2153,"cache_read_input_tokens":148119,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":2153,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":279},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4d21e41c-7b8c-412a-ac18-df8336bdf9ca","uuid":"e467afbc-07e4-45d7-a464-7f2396e6c70b"}
