{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01SDK85GJeuqmN9uTpgWFVrc","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?>\n     2→<beans xmlns=\"https://jakarta.ee/xml/ns/jakartaee\"\n     3→       xmlns:xsi=\"http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance\"\n     4→       xsi:schemaLocation=\"https://jakarta.ee/xml/ns/jakartaee https://jakarta.ee/xml/ns/jakartaee/beans_4_0.xsd\"\n     5→       version=\"4.0\"\n     6→       bean-discovery-mode=\"annotated\">\n     7→    <interceptors>\n     8→        <class>org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.transaction.TransactionalInterceptor</class>\n     9→    </interceptors>\n    10→</beans>\n    11→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4d21e41c-7b8c-412a-ac18-df8336bdf9ca","uuid":"9a526139-6d59-4efe-bbba-e7d2dd5bd137"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01REABthJHVfrrnqDqihzUa9","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Wait, the problem is that with `annotated` mode, only classes with bean-defining annotations like `@ApplicationScoped` are discovered. `EntityUtils` has `@ApplicationScoped` so it should be discovered. The issue is that `EntityUtils` has `@AllArgsConstructor` which creates a constructor with parameters `UserModelBuilder`, `TagBuilder`, `ArticleModelBuilder`, `CommentBuilder`. These are **not CDI beans** - they are produced by the configuration classes (`UsersConfiguration`, `ArticlesConfiguration`, etc.) as `@Singleton @Produces` methods.\n\nThe issue is likely that the beans.xml with `annotated` mode can't see the configuration classes because `@Dependent` is a CDI scope annotation. Let me check if the configuration classes are being detected. Also, the `EntityUtils` issue could be that it's using Lombok `@AllArgsConstructor` but Weld needs `@Inject` on the constructor.\n\nThe fix: I need to add `@Inject` to the constructor. Since `@AllArgsConstructor` doesn't add `@Inject`, I need to use `@AllArgsConstructor(onConstructor_ = {@jakarta.inject.Inject})` or switch to field injection. Let me just switch EntityUtils and the resource classes to use `@Inject` on fields:"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":573,"cache_read_input_tokens":150272,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":573,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":464},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4d21e41c-7b8c-412a-ac18-df8336bdf9ca","uuid":"d3e7669d-4ea0-4f3a-b643-248498f6527c"}
