{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01XXWtt4ZAY3TR1ERmV6wsyk","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The problem is complex. The domain/feature/impl classes aren't CDI beans (they're constructed manually in the Configuration classes). But the CDI-managed classes like `EntityUtils`, resource classes, `ResourceUtils`, and `SlugifySlugProvider` use `@AllArgsConstructor` for constructor injection. In Weld SE, constructor injection requires `@Inject` on the constructor.\n\nThe easiest fix is to use `lombok.config` to make `@AllArgsConstructor` add `@Inject`:"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1867,"cache_read_input_tokens":151632,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1867,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":276},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4d21e41c-7b8c-412a-ac18-df8336bdf9ca","uuid":"510573de-b181-40a6-b088-820b0ebae946"}
