{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_013DApTbmU3gFDmWuHbk18UU","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Actually, `@ConstructorProperties` won't help with CDI. The fix is more direct - I need CDI to find the right constructor. Let me change the CDI-managed classes that use `@AllArgsConstructor` to also have `@Inject` on the constructor. The cleanest approach is to use Lombok's `onConstructor_` feature:\n\nFor the CDI-managed beans with `@AllArgsConstructor`, I need to change them to `@AllArgsConstructor(onConstructor_ = @Inject)`. But there's a subtlety - domain classes like `User`, `Article` etc. aren't CDI beans, so they don't need this.\n\nLet me identify which classes are CDI beans and fix only those:"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":605,"cache_read_input_tokens":153499,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":605,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":387},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4d21e41c-7b8c-412a-ac18-df8336bdf9ca","uuid":"7c931179-1cfe-4e4b-9c7b-7e3ea38bd2e5"}
