domain/feature/impl/DeleteArticleBySlugImpl.java\n- org/example/realworldapi/domain/feature/impl/CreateUserImpl.java\n- org/example/realworldapi/domain/feature/impl/CreateTagImpl.java\n- org/example/realworldapi/domain/feature/impl/CreateSlugByTitleImpl.java\n- org/example/realworldapi/domain/feature/impl/CreateCommentImpl.java\n- org/example/realworldapi/domain/feature/impl/CreateArticleImpl.java\n- org/example/realworldapi/domain/feature/impl/ArticleFavoritesCountImpl.java\n\nFor each file:\n1. Read the file\n2. Check if it has `@AllArgsConstructor` AND is a CDI bean (has @ApplicationScoped, @RequestScoped, @Dependent, @Singleton, or @Path annotation)\n3. If so:\n   a. Replace `@AllArgsConstructor` with `@AllArgsConstructor(onConstructor_ = @Inject)`\n   b. Add `import jakarta.inject.Inject;` if not already present (add it near other jakarta imports or near other import statements)\n4. Do NOT modify files that are pure data classes (no CDI scope annotation and no @Path) - these just use @AllArgsConstructor for convenience and don't need @Inject\n\nIMPORTANT: Also check the domain/feature/impl files - they likely have @ApplicationScoped. Fix them too.\n\nAlso IMPORTANT: Some files might not have @AllArgsConstructor but still need CDI fixes. The repository classes (ArticleRepositoryPanache, etc.) already use field injection with @Inject, so they should be fine. Focus only on classes that use @AllArgsConstructor for constructor injection.\n\nPlease read each file first before editing it. Process ALL the files listed above. Report back which files you modified and which you skipped (and why)."}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1171,"cache_read_input_tokens":25450,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1171,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":1776},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4d21e41c-7b8c-412a-ac18-df8336bdf9ca","uuid":"832bdc17-9aed-499c-bbc