{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01NCxvBdxa6F6Bf7op2UExgs","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.repository.hibernate.entity;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\n     4→import lombok.AllArgsConstructor;\n     5→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article.Article;\n     6→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article.ArticleModelBuilder;\n     7→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article.FavoriteRelationship;\n     8→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.comment.Comment;\n     9→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.comment.CommentBuilder;\n    10→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.tag.Tag;\n    11→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.tag.TagBuilder;\n    12→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.user.User;\n    13→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.user.UserModelBuilder;\n    14→\n    15→@ApplicationScoped\n    16→@AllArgsConstructor\n    17→public class EntityUtils {\n    18→  private final UserModelBuilder userBuilder;\n    19→  private final TagBuilder tagBuilder;\n    20→  private final ArticleModelBuilder articleBuilder;\n    21→  private final CommentBuilder commentBuilder;\n    22→\n    23→  public User user(UserEntity userEntity) {\n    24→    final var id = userEntity.getId();\n    25→    final var username = userEntity.getUsername();\n    26→    final var bio = userEntity.getBio();\n    27→    final var image = userEntity.getImage();\n    28→    final var password = userEntity.getPassword();\n    29→    final var email = userEntity.getEmail();\n    30→    return userBuilder.build(id, username, bio, image, password, email);\n    31→  }\n    32→\n    33→  public Tag tag(TagEntity tagEntity) {\n    34→    return tagBuilder.build(tagEntity.getId(), tagEntity.getName());\n    35→  }\n    36→\n    37→  public Tag tag(TagRelationshipEntity tagRelationshipEntity) {\n    38→    return tag(tagRelationshipEntity.getPrimaryKey().getTag());\n    39→  }\n    40→\n    41→  public Article article(ArticleEntity articleEntity) {\n    42→    return articleBuilder.build(\n    43→        articleEntity.getId(),\n    44→        articleEntity.getSlug(),\n    45→        articleEntity.getTitle(),\n    46→        articleEntity.getDescription(),\n    47→        articleEntity.getBody(),\n    48→        articleEntity.getCreatedAt(),\n    49→        articleEntity.getUpdatedAt(),\n    50→        user(articleEntity.getAuthor()));\n    51→  }\n    52→\n    53→  public Comment comment(CommentEntity commentEntity) {\n    54→    return commentBuilder.build(\n    55→        commentEntity.getId(),\n    56→        user(commentEntity.getAuthor()),\n    57→        article(commentEntity.getArticle()),\n    58→        commentEntity.getBody(),\n    59→        commentEntity.getCreatedAt(),\n    60→        commentEntity.getUpdatedAt());\n    61→  }\n    62→\n    63→  public FavoriteRelationship favoriteRelationship(\n    64→      FavoriteRelationshipEntity favoriteRelationshipEntity) {\n    65→    return new FavoriteRelationship(\n    66→        user(favoriteRelationshipEntity.getUser()),\n    67→        article(favoriteRelationshipEntity.getArticle()));\n    68→  }\n    69→}\n    70→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_014TjWyNSwtQyHDxeJKs7YUX","session_id":"4d21e41c-7b8c-412a-ac18-df8336bdf9ca","uuid":"1f00931d-6069-4f6e-ade6-dd1cfaee728c"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01LASBMFb9RyKsJrnT3XufTh","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.provider;\n     2→\n     3→import com.github.slugify.Slugify;\n     4→import jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\n     5→import lombok.AllArgsConstructor;\n     6→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.provider.SlugProvider;\n     7→\n     8→@ApplicationScoped\n     9→@AllArgsConstructor\n    10→public class SlugifySlugProvider implements SlugProvider {\n    11→\n    12→  private final Slugify slugify;\n    13→\n    14→  @Override\n    15→  public String slugify(String text) {\n    16→    return slugify.slugify(text);\n    17→  }\n    18→}\n    19→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_014TjWyNSwtQyHDxeJKs7YUX","session_id":"4d21e41c-7b8c-412a-ac18-df8336bdf9ca","uuid":"118bedfd-b11b-40ed-8ccf-4bfd63449ad9"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01SR6xTcZvywjCXHsM8mW27E","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.application.web.resource.utils;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\n     4→import jakarta.ws.rs.core.SecurityContext;\n     5→import java.security.Principal;\n     6→import java.util.List;\n     7→import java.util.UUID;\n     8→import java.util.stream.Collectors;\n     9→import lombok.AllArgsConstructor;\n    10→import org.example.realworldapi.application.web.model.response.*;\n    11→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.*;\n    12→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article.Article;\n    13→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article.PageResult;\n    14→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.comment.Comment;\n    15→\n    16→@ApplicationScoped\n    17→@AllArgsConstructor\n    18→public class ResourceUtils {\n    19→\n    20→  private static final int DEFAULT_LIMIT = 20;\n    21→  private final FindUserByUsername findUserByUsername;\n    22→  private final IsFollowingUser isFollowingUser;\n    23→  private final FindArticleTags findArticleTags;\n    24→  private final IsArticleFavorited isArticleFavorited;\n    25→  private final ArticleFavoritesCount articleFavoritesCount;\n    26→\n    27→  public ProfileResponse profileResponse(String username, UUID loggedUserId) {\n    28→    final var user = findUserByUsername.handle(username);\n    29→    final var profileResponse = new ProfileResponse(user);\n    30→    if (loggedUserId != null) {\n    31→      profileResponse.setFollowing(isFollowingUser.handle(loggedUserId, user.getId()));\n    32→    }\n    33→    return profileResponse;\n    34→  }\n    35→\n    36→  public ArticleResponse articleResponse(Article article, UUID loggedUserId) {\n    37→    final var author = article.getAuthor();\n    38→    final var profileResponse = profileResponse(author.getUsername(), author.getId());\n    39→    final var tags = findArticleTags.handle(article);\n    40→    final var favoritesCount = articleFavoritesCount.handle(article.getId());\n    41→    final var articleResponse = new ArticleResponse(article, profileResponse, favoritesCount, tags);\n    42→    if (loggedUserId != null) {\n    43→      articleResponse.setFavorited(isArticleFavorited.handle(article, loggedUserId));\n    44→    }\n    45→    return articleResponse;\n    46→  }\n    47→\n    48→  public ArticlesResponse articlesResponse(PageResult<Article> pageResult, UUID loggedUserId) {\n    49→    final var resultResponse =\n    50→        pageResult.getResult().stream()\n    51→            .map(article -> articleResponse(article, loggedUserId))\n    52→            .collect(Collectors.toList());\n    53→    return new ArticlesResponse(resultResponse, pageResult.getTotal());\n    54→  }\n    55→\n    56→  public CommentResponse commentResponse(Comment comment, UUID loggedUserId) {\n    57→    final var commentAuthor = comment.getAuthor();\n    58→    final var authorResponse = profileResponse(commentAuthor.getUsername(), loggedUserId);\n    59→    return new CommentResponse(comment, authorResponse);\n    60→  }\n    61→\n    62→  public UUID getLoggedUserId(SecurityContext securityContext) {\n    63→    Principal principal = securityContext.getUserPrincipal();\n    64→    return principal != null ? UUID.fromString(principal.getName()) : null;\n    65→  }\n    66→\n    67→  public CommentsResponse commentsResponse(List<Comment> comments, UUID loggedUserId) {\n    68→    final var resultResponse =\n    69→        comments.stream()\n    70→            .map(comment -> commentResponse(comment, loggedUserId))\n    71→            .collect(Collectors.toList());\n    72→    return new CommentsResponse(resultResponse);\n    73→  }\n    74→\n    75→  public int getLimit(int limit) {\n    76→    return limit > 0 ? limit : DEFAULT_LIMIT;\n    77→  }\n    78→}\n    79→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_014TjWyNSwtQyHDxeJKs7YUX","session_id":"4d21e41c-7b8c-412a-ac18-df8336bdf9ca","uuid":"34bb2eeb-e87b-4ac0-8d22-23e0837fcfbf"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Q1mxYCyLws5y1TgQU3WtYP","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.domain.validator;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.validation.ConstraintViolation;\n     4→import jakarta.validation.Validator;\n     5→import java.util.Set;\n     6→import java.util.stream.Collectors;\n     7→import lombok.AllArgsConstructor;\n     8→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.exception.ModelValidationException;\n     9→\n    10→@AllArgsConstructor\n    11→public class ModelValidator {\n    12→\n    13→  private final Validator validator;\n    14→\n    15→  public <T> T validate(T model) {\n    16→    Set<ConstraintViolation<T>> constraintViolations = validator.validate(model);\n    17→\n    18→    if (!constraintViolations.isEmpty()) {\n    19→      final var messages =\n    20→          constraintViolations.stream()\n    21→              .map(ConstraintViolation::getMessage)\n    22→              .collect(Collectors.toList());\n    23→      throw new ModelValidationException(messages);\n    24→    }\n    25→\n    26→    return model;\n    27→  }\n    28→}\n    29→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_014TjWyNSwtQyHDxeJKs7YUX","session_id":"4d21e41c-7b8c-412a-ac18-df8336bdf9ca","uuid":"b7fb181c-9648-47fb-b248-e42b6d634c02"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01HFiQUiNAqGQUG4qjbU2oft","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.user;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.inject.Named;\n     4→import java.util.UUID;\n     5→import lombok.AllArgsConstructor;\n     6→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.validator.ModelValidator;\n     7→\n     8→@Named\n     9→@AllArgsConstructor\n    10→public class UserModelBuilder {\n    11→  private final ModelValidator modelValidator;\n    12→\n    13→  public User build(String username, String email, String password) {\n    14→    return modelValidator.validate(\n    15→        new User(UUID.randomUUID(), username, email, password, null, null));\n    16→  }\n    17→\n    18→  public User build(\n    19→      UUID id, String username, String bio, String image, String password, String email) {\n    20→    return modelValidator.validate(new User(id, username, email, password, bio, image));\n    21→  }\n    22→}\n    23→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_014TjWyNSwtQyHDxeJKs7YUX","session_id":"4d21e41c-7b8c-412a-ac18-df8336bdf9ca","uuid":"83b16951-8d15-41d5-afcb-84a178a37745"}
