{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_014TjWyNSwtQyHDxeJKs7YUX","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! All files have been modified correctly. Now let me create a comprehensive summary report:\n\n## Summary of Weld CDI Injection Fixes\n\nI have successfully fixed the Weld CDI injection issues in the Jakarta EE application. The problem was that Lombok's `@AllArgsConstructor` generates constructors without the `@Inject` annotation, which Weld requires for CDI constructor injection.\n\n### Files Modified (9 total)\n\nAll CDI-managed beans that use `@AllArgsConstructor` for constructor injection have been updated with the following changes:\n\n1. **Changed** `@AllArgsConstructor` to `@AllArgsConstructor(onConstructor_ = @Inject)`\n2. **Added** `import jakarta.inject.Inject;` to the import statements\n\n#### CDI Beans with @ApplicationScoped (4 files):\n\n1. **/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__realworld__quarkus__jakarta/run_1/output/src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/infrastructure/repository/hibernate/entity/EntityUtils.java**\n   - Has `@ApplicationScoped` annotation\n   - Updated with `onConstructor_ = @Inject`\n\n2. **/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__realworld__quarkus__jakarta/run_1/output/src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/infrastructure/provider/SlugifySlugProvider.java**\n   - Has `@ApplicationScoped` annotation\n   - Updated with `onConstructor_ = @Inject`\n\n3. **/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__realworld__quarkus__jakarta/run_1/output/src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/application/web/resource/utils/ResourceUtils.java**\n   - Has `@ApplicationScoped` annotation\n   - Updated with `onConstructor_ = @Inject`\n\n4. **/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__realworld__quarkus__jakarta/run_1/output/src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/domain/model/user/UserModelBuilder.java**\n   - Has `@Named` annotation (CDI qualifier)\n   - Updated with `onConstructor_ = @Inject`\n\n#### JAX-RS Resources with @Path (5 files):\n\n5. **/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__realworld__quarkus__jakarta/run_1/output/src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/application/web/resource/ArticlesResource.java**\n   - Has `@Path(\"/articles\")` annotation\n   - Updated with `onConstructor_ = @Inject`\n\n6. **/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__realworld__quarkus__jakarta/run_1/output/src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/application/web/resource/UsersResource.java**\n   - Has `@Path(\"/users\")` annotation\n   - Updated with `onConstructor_ = @Inject`\n\n7. **/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__realworld__quarkus__jakarta/run_1/output/src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/application/web/resource/UserResource.java**\n   - Has `@Path(\"/user\")` annotation\n   - Updated with `onConstructor_ = @Inject`\n\n8. **/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__realworld__quarkus__jakarta/run_1/output/src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/application/web/resource/ProfilesResource.java**\n   - Has `@Path(\"/profiles\")` annotation\n   - Updated with `onConstructor_ = @Inject`\n\n9. **/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__realworld__quarkus__jakarta/run_1/output/src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/application/web/resource/TagsResource.java**\n   - Has `@Path(\"/tags\")` annotation\n   - Updated with `onConstructor_ = @Inject`\n\n### Files Skipped (Correctly NOT Modified)\n\nThe following files were analyzed but correctly NOT modified because they are **not** CDI-managed beans. These classes are instantiated via `@Produces` methods in configuration classes and do not need `@Inject` on their constructors:\n\n- **TagBuilder.java** - No CDI scope annotation, instantiated via @Produces in configuration\n- **CommentBuilder.java** - No CDI scope annotation, instantiated via @Produces in configuration  \n- **ArticleModelBuilder.java** - No CDI scope annotation, instantiated via @Produces in configuration\n- **ModelValidator.java** - No CDI scope annotation, instantiated via @Produces in configuration\n- **All domain/feature/impl/*.java files** (30+ files) - No CDI scope annotations, all instantiated via @Produces methods in configuration classes (UsersConfiguration, ArticlesConfiguration, CommentsConfiguration, TagsConfiguration)\n\n### Technical Details\n\nThe fix uses Lombok's `onConstructor_` feature to add the `@Inject` annotation to the generated constructor. The syntax:\n\n```java\n@AllArgsConstructor(onConstructor_ = @Inject)\n```\n\nThis tells Lombok to generate a constructor like:\n\n```java\n@Inject\npublic ClassName(Dependency1 dep1, Dependency2 dep2, ...) {\n    this.dep1 = dep1;\n    this.dep2 = dep2;\n    ...\n}\n```\n\nThis ensures that Weld CDI can properly inject dependencies into these beans at runtime."}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4d21e41c-7b8c-412a-ac18-df8336bdf9ca","uuid":"10bdbfb3-ec57-4281-bf27-325094c13d52"}
