{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Psh6BcdzBkhE849VGfqiPH","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.configuration;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.enterprise.context.Dependent;\n     4→import jakarta.enterprise.inject.Produces;\n     5→import jakarta.inject.Singleton;\n     6→import jakarta.validation.Validator;\n     7→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.*;\n     8→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.impl.*;\n     9→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.provider.HashProvider;\n    10→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.user.FollowRelationshipRepository;\n    11→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.user.UserModelBuilder;\n    12→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.user.UserRepository;\n    13→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.validator.ModelValidator;\n    14→\n    15→@Dependent\n    16→public class UsersConfiguration {\n    17→\n    18→  @Produces\n    19→  @Singleton\n    20→  public CreateUser createUser(\n    21→      UserRepository userRepository, HashProvider hashProvider, UserModelBuilder userBuilder) {\n    22→    return new CreateUserImpl(userRepository, hashProvider, userBuilder);\n    23→  }\n    24→\n    25→  @Produces\n    26→  @Singleton\n    27→  public UpdateUser updateUser(\n    28→      FindUserById findUserById, UserRepository userRepository, ModelValidator modelValidator) {\n    29→    return new UpdateUserImpl(findUserById, userRepository, modelValidator);\n    30→  }\n    31→\n    32→  @Produces\n    33→  @Singleton\n    34→  public FindUserById findUserById(UserRepository userRepository) {\n    35→    return new FindUserByIdImpl(userRepository);\n    36→  }\n    37→\n    38→  @Produces\n    39→  @Singleton\n    40→  public LoginUser loginUser(UserRepository userRepository, HashProvider hashProvider) {\n    41→    return new LoginUserImpl(userRepository, hashProvider);\n    42→  }\n    43→\n    44→  @Produces\n    45→  @Singleton\n    46→  public FindUserByUsername findUserByUsername(UserRepository userRepository) {\n    47→    return new FindUserByUsernameImpl(userRepository);\n    48→  }\n    49→\n    50→  @Produces\n    51→  @Singleton\n    52→  public IsFollowingUser isFollowingUser(FollowRelationshipRepository usersFollowedRepository) {\n    53→    return new IsFollowingUserImpl(usersFollowedRepository);\n    54→  }\n    55→\n    56→  @Produces\n    57→  @Singleton\n    58→  public FollowUserByUsername followUserByUsername(\n    59→      FindUserById findUserById,\n    60→      FindUserByUsername findUserByUsername,\n    61→      FollowRelationshipRepository followRelationshipRepository) {\n    62→    return new FollowUserByUsernameImpl(\n    63→        findUserById, findUserByUsername, followRelationshipRepository);\n    64→  }\n    65→\n    66→  @Produces\n    67→  @Singleton\n    68→  public UnfollowUserByUsername unfollowUserByUsername(\n    69→      FindUserById findUserById,\n    70→      FindUserByUsername findUserByUsername,\n    71→      FollowRelationshipRepository followRelationshipRepository) {\n    72→    return new UnfollowUserByUsernameImpl(\n    73→        findUserById, findUserByUsername, followRelationshipRepository);\n    74→  }\n    75→\n    76→  @Produces\n    77→  @Singleton\n    78→  public UserModelBuilder userModelBuilder(ModelValidator modelValidator) {\n    79→    return new UserModelBuilder(modelValidator);\n    80→  }\n    81→\n    82→  @Produces\n    83→  @Singleton\n    84→  public ModelValidator modelValidator(Validator validator) {\n    85→    return new ModelValidator(validator);\n    86→  }\n    87→}\n    88→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4d21e41c-7b8c-412a-ac18-df8336bdf9ca","uuid":"e925801d-52d8-4b2f-a2ca-a7da1d0c5c2a"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01Xqi5qZTEnUeU45N1MLbDnG","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I see an important issue. `UserModelBuilder` has both `@Named` with `@AllArgsConstructor(onConstructor_ = @Inject)`, BUT it's also being produced by a `@Produces` method in `UsersConfiguration` (line 78-80). This creates an **ambiguous dependency** - Weld will see two ways to create a `UserModelBuilder`: via the `@Named` annotation on the class itself, and via the `@Produces` method. Same issue likely exists for `ModelValidator`.\n\nI need to either:\n1. Remove the `@Named` and `@AllArgsConstructor(onConstructor_ = @Inject)` from `UserModelBuilder` (since it's produced by config), OR\n2. Remove the `@Produces` method from the configuration\n\nSince the configuration classes explicitly construct these via `@Produces`, I should remove CDI annotations from the class itself. Let me also check other configuration classes and builders."}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2946,"cache_read_input_tokens":36041,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":2946,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":876},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4d21e41c-7b8c-412a-ac18-df8336bdf9ca","uuid":"bc92675f-6887-4f9f-9770-dc1e421dec31"}
