{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01NcotNnSapAUZNSZV3wSqGx","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The error is clear now: `WELD-001435: Normal scoped bean class EntityUtils is not proxyable because it has no no-args constructor`. \n\nFor `@ApplicationScoped` beans (normal scoped), Weld creates a proxy, and the proxy class needs a no-arg constructor. With `@AllArgsConstructor(onConstructor_ = @Inject)`, Lombok only generates the all-args constructor. I need to also add `@NoArgsConstructor` to these CDI beans, or use `@lombok.NoArgsConstructor(access = AccessLevel.PACKAGE)`.\n\nLet me fix all CDI beans that have `@ApplicationScoped` - they all need a no-arg constructor for proxying:"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1576,"cache_read_input_tokens":89562,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1576,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":1208},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4d21e41c-7b8c-412a-ac18-df8336bdf9ca","uuid":"d306ab54-a1cb-48dd-9b12-e1b03bee4443"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01NcotNnSapAUZNSZV3wSqGx","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_bdrk_013YNiymSTA2QresjPvBV7Gd","name":"Task","input":{"description":"Add @NoArgsConstructor to CDI beans","subagent_type":"general-purpose","prompt":"I need to fix Weld CDI proxy issues in a Jakarta EE application. The problem is that `@ApplicationScoped` beans (normal-scoped) require a no-arg constructor for Weld to create proxies.\n\nFor every file that has `@ApplicationScoped` AND `@AllArgsConstructor(onConstructor_ = @Inject)`, I need to ALSO add `@NoArgsConstructor` from Lombok.\n\nThe base directory is: /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__realworld__quarkus__jakarta/run_1/output/src/main/java\n\nThe affected files are CDI beans with @ApplicationScoped that already have @AllArgsConstructor(onConstructor_ = @Inject):\n\n1. org/example/realworldapi/infrastructure/repository/hibernate/entity/EntityUtils.java\n2. org/example/realworldapi/infrastructure/provider/SlugifySlugProvider.java \n3. org/example/realworldapi/application/web/resource/utils/ResourceUtils.java\n\nFor the JAX-RS @Path resources (which don't have a CDI scope annotation but need to be CDI-managed), they also need a no-arg constructor:\n\n4. org/example/realworldapi/application/web/resource/ArticlesResource.java\n5. org/example/realworldapi/application/web/resource/UsersResource.java\n6. org/example/realworldapi/application/web/resource/UserResource.java\n7. org/example/realworldapi/application/web/resource/ProfilesResource.java\n8. org/example/realworldapi/application/web/resource/TagsResource.java\n\nAlso check these infrastructure classes - they might also be @ApplicationScoped:\n9. org/example/realworldapi/infrastructure/provider/JwtTokenProvider.java\n10. org/example/realworldapi/infrastructure/provider/BCryptHashProvider.java\n\nFor each file:\n1. Read the file\n2. If it has @AllArgsConstructor (with or without onConstructor_), add `@NoArgsConstructor` annotation\n3. Add `import lombok.NoArgsConstructor;` if not already present\n4. Place @NoArgsConstructor right before @AllArgsConstructor\n\nExample transformation:\n```java\nimport lombok.AllArgsConstructor;\nimport lombok.NoArgsConstructor;\n\n@ApplicationScoped\n@NoArgsConstructor\n@AllArgsConstructor(onConstructor_ = @Inject)\npublic class EntityUtils {\n```\n\nALSO check the repository classes. They are @ApplicationScoped and extend AbstractPanacheRepository. They need no-arg constructors too. The repo files are:\n- org/example/realworldapi/infrastructure/repository/hibernate/panache/ArticleRepositoryPanache.java\n- org/example/realworldapi/infrastructure/repository/hibernate/panache/UserRepositoryPanache.java\n- org/example/realworldapi/infrastructure/repository/hibernate/panache/CommentRepositoryPanache.java\n- org/example/realworldapi/infrastructure/repository/hibernate/panache/TagRepositoryPanache.java\n- org/example/realworldapi/infrastructure/repository/hibernate/panache/FollowRelationshipRepositoryPanache.java\n- org/example/realworldapi/infrastructure/repository/hibernate/panache/FavoriteRelationshipRepositoryPanache.java\n- org/example/realworldapi/infrastructure/repository/hibernate/panache/TagRelationshipRepositoryPanache.java\n\nAlso check their parent class:\n- org/example/realworldapi/infrastructure/repository/hibernate/panache/AbstractPanacheRepository.java\n\nRead each file first. If any of these already has a no-arg constructor, skip it. Otherwise, add the constructor or @NoArgsConstructor annotation as appropriate.\n\nReport back all changes made."}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1576,"cache_read_input_tokens":89562,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1576,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":1208},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4d21e41c-7b8c-412a-ac18-df8336bdf9ca","uuid":"e3658759-c42d-45df-9d7f-e90d49e411b2"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I need to fix Weld CDI proxy issues in a Jakarta EE application. The problem is that `@ApplicationScoped` beans (normal-scoped) require a no-arg constructor for Weld to create proxies.\n\nFor every file that has `@ApplicationScoped` AND `@AllArgsConstructor(onConstructor_ = @Inject)`, I need to ALSO add `@NoArgsConstructor` from Lombok.\n\nThe base directory is: /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__realworld__quarkus__jakarta/run_1/output/src/main/java\n\nThe affected files are CDI beans with @ApplicationScoped that already have @AllArgsConstructor(onConstructor_ = @Inject):\n\n1. org/example/realworldapi/infrastructure/repository/hibernate/entity/EntityUtils.java\n2. org/example/realworldapi/infrastructure/provider/SlugifySlugProvider.java \n3. org/example/realworldapi/application/web/resource/utils/ResourceUtils.java\n\nFor the JAX-RS @Path resources (which don't have a CDI scope annotation but need to be CDI-managed), they also need a no-arg constructor:\n\n4. org/example/realworldapi/application/web/resource/ArticlesResource.java\n5. org/example/realworldapi/application/web/resource/UsersResource.java\n6. org/example/realworldapi/application/web/resource/UserResource.java\n7. org/example/realworldapi/application/web/resource/ProfilesResource.java\n8. org/example/realworldapi/application/web/resource/TagsResource.java\n\nAlso check these infrastructure classes - they might also be @ApplicationScoped:\n9. org/example/realworldapi/infrastructure/provider/JwtTokenProvider.java\n10. org/example/realworldapi/infrastructure/provider/BCryptHashProvider.java\n\nFor each file:\n1. Read the file\n2. If it has @AllArgsConstructor (with or without onConstructor_), add `@NoArgsConstructor` annotation\n3. Add `import lombok.NoArgsConstructor;` if not already present\n4. Place @NoArgsConstructor right before @AllArgsConstructor\n\nExample transformation:\n```java\nimport lombok.AllArgsConstructor;\nimport lombok.NoArgsConstructor;\n\n@ApplicationScoped\n@NoArgsConstructor\n@AllArgsConstructor(onConstructor_ = @Inject)\npublic class EntityUtils {\n```\n\nALSO check the repository classes. They are @ApplicationScoped and extend AbstractPanacheRepository. They need no-arg constructors too. The repo files are:\n- org/example/realworldapi/infrastructure/repository/hibernate/panache/ArticleRepositoryPanache.java\n- org/example/realworldapi/infrastructure/repository/hibernate/panache/UserRepositoryPanache.java\n- org/example/realworldapi/infrastructure/repository/hibernate/panache/CommentRepositoryPanache.java\n- org/example/realworldapi/infrastructure/repository/hibernate/panache/TagRepositoryPanache.java\n- org/example/realworldapi/infrastructure/repository/hibernate/panache/FollowRelationshipRepositoryPanache.java\n- org/example/realworldapi/infrastructure/repository/hibernate/panache/FavoriteRelationshipRepositoryPanache.java\n- org/example/realworldapi/infrastructure/repository/hibernate/panache/TagRelationshipRepositoryPanache.java\n\nAlso check their parent class:\n- org/example/realworldapi/infrastructure/repository/hibernate/panache/AbstractPanacheRepository.java\n\nRead each file first. If any of these already has a no-arg constructor, skip it. Otherwise, add the constructor or @NoArgsConstructor annotation as appropriate.\n\nReport back all changes made."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_013YNiymSTA2QresjPvBV7Gd","session_id":"4d21e41c-7b8c-412a-ac18-df8336bdf9ca","uuid":"516e31ac-1423-411b-af19-d80c227d351a"}
