{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01NynfB64aQfEyuoThhUichf","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.application.web.resource;\n     2→\n     3→import com.fasterxml.jackson.core.JsonProcessingException;\n     4→import com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.ObjectMapper;\n     5→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n     6→import jakarta.ws.rs.GET;\n     7→import jakarta.ws.rs.Path;\n     8→import jakarta.ws.rs.Produces;\n     9→import jakarta.ws.rs.core.MediaType;\n    10→import jakarta.ws.rs.core.Response;\n    11→import java.util.List;\n    12→import lombok.AllArgsConstructor;\n    13→import org.example.realworldapi.application.web.model.response.TagsResponse;\n    14→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.FindTags;\n    15→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.tag.Tag;\n    16→import org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.web.qualifiers.NoWrapRootValueObjectMapper;\n    17→\n    18→@Path(\"/tags\")\n    19→@AllArgsConstructor(onConstructor_ = @Inject)\n    20→public class TagsResource {\n    21→\n    22→  @NoWrapRootValueObjectMapper ObjectMapper objectMapper;\n    23→  private final FindTags findTags;\n    24→\n    25→  @GET\n    26→  @Produces(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON)\n    27→  public Response getTags() throws JsonProcessingException {\n    28→    List<Tag> tags = findTags.handle();\n    29→    return Response.ok(objectMapper.writeValueAsString(new TagsResponse(tags)))\n    30→        .status(Response.Status.OK)\n    31→        .build();\n    32→  }\n    33→}\n    34→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_013YNiymSTA2QresjPvBV7Gd","session_id":"4d21e41c-7b8c-412a-ac18-df8336bdf9ca","uuid":"73ff3efc-8dac-404d-ac70-8df08d88f5dc"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Wfimkhvia3k4VMGxc2DWBU","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.provider;\n     2→\n     3→import com.nimbusds.jose.*;\n     4→import com.nimbusds.jose.crypto.RSASSASigner;\n     5→import com.nimbusds.jwt.JWTClaimsSet;\n     6→import com.nimbusds.jwt.SignedJWT;\n     7→import jakarta.annotation.PostConstruct;\n     8→import jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\n     9→import java.io.InputStream;\n    10→import java.security.KeyFactory;\n    11→import java.security.interfaces.RSAPrivateKey;\n    12→import java.security.spec.PKCS8EncodedKeySpec;\n    13→import java.util.*;\n    14→\n    15→@ApplicationScoped\n    16→public class JwtTokenProvider {\n    17→\n    18→  private RSAPrivateKey privateKey;\n    19→\n    20→  @PostConstruct\n    21→  public void init() {\n    22→    try {\n    23→      privateKey = loadPrivateKey();\n    24→    } catch (Exception e) {\n    25→      throw new RuntimeException(\"Failed to load private key\", e);\n    26→    }\n    27→  }\n    28→\n    29→  private RSAPrivateKey loadPrivateKey() throws Exception {\n    30→    try (InputStream is =\n    31→        Thread.currentThread().getContextClassLoader().getResourceAsStream(\"privateKey.pem\")) {\n    32→      if (is == null) {\n    33→        throw new RuntimeException(\"privateKey.pem not found on classpath\");\n    34→      }\n    35→      String pem = new String(is.readAllBytes());\n    36→      pem =\n    37→          pem.replace(\"-----BEGIN PRIVATE KEY-----\", \"\")\n    38→              .replace(\"-----END PRIVATE KEY-----\", \"\")\n    39→              .replaceAll(\"\\\\s\", \"\");\n    40→      byte[] decoded = Base64.getDecoder().decode(pem);\n    41→      PKCS8EncodedKeySpec spec = new PKCS8EncodedKeySpec(decoded);\n    42→      KeyFactory kf = KeyFactory.getInstance(\"RSA\");\n    43→      return (RSAPrivateKey) kf.generatePrivate(spec);\n    44→    }\n    45→  }\n    46→\n    47→  public String createUserToken(String subject) {\n    48→    try {\n    49→      JWTClaimsSet claims =\n    50→          new JWTClaimsSet.Builder()\n    51→              .issuer(\"users-service\")\n    52→              .subject(subject)\n    53→              .claim(\"groups\", List.of(\"USER\"))\n    54→              .expirationTime(new Date(System.currentTimeMillis() + 86400000))\n    55→              .issueTime(new Date())\n    56→              .build();\n    57→\n    58→      JWSHeader header =\n    59→          new JWSHeader.Builder(JWSAlgorithm.RS256).type(JOSEObjectType.JWT).build();\n    60→\n    61→      SignedJWT signedJWT = new SignedJWT(header, claims);\n    62→      signedJWT.sign(new RSASSASigner(privateKey));\n    63→\n    64→      return signedJWT.serialize();\n    65→    } catch (Exception e) {\n    66→      throw new RuntimeException(\"Failed to create JWT token\", e);\n    67→    }\n    68→  }\n    69→}\n    70→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_013YNiymSTA2QresjPvBV7Gd","session_id":"4d21e41c-7b8c-412a-ac18-df8336bdf9ca","uuid":"52e4e2d2-b80a-4acf-82cd-5f58dc1fa2dd"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01PvcNw6hRaRvNn4kGB7eMt9","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.provider;\n     2→\n     3→import at.favre.lib.crypto.bcrypt.BCrypt;\n     4→import jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\n     5→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.provider.HashProvider;\n     6→\n     7→@ApplicationScoped\n     8→public class BCryptHashProvider implements HashProvider {\n     9→\n    10→  @Override\n    11→  public String hashPassword(String password) {\n    12→    return BCrypt.withDefaults().hashToString(12, password.toCharArray());\n    13→  }\n    14→\n    15→  @Override\n    16→  public boolean checkPassword(String plaintext, String hashed) {\n    17→    BCrypt.Result result = BCrypt.verifyer().verify(plaintext.toCharArray(), hashed);\n    18→    return result.verified;\n    19→  }\n    20→}\n    21→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_013YNiymSTA2QresjPvBV7Gd","session_id":"4d21e41c-7b8c-412a-ac18-df8336bdf9ca","uuid":"3a7c4562-3548-4ec1-b56e-c40bda23b1d8"}
