{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01WSZxErLgdSF7DK9iR1Ym3t","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.repository.hibernate.entity;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\n     4→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n     5→import lombok.AllArgsConstructor;\n     6→import lombok.NoArgsConstructor;\n     7→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article.Article;\n     8→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article.ArticleModelBuilder;\n     9→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article.FavoriteRelationship;\n    10→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.comment.Comment;\n    11→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.comment.CommentBuilder;\n    12→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.tag.Tag;\n    13→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.tag.TagBuilder;\n    14→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.user.User;\n    15→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.user.UserModelBuilder;\n    16→\n    17→@ApplicationScoped\n    18→@NoArgsConstructor\n    19→@AllArgsConstructor(onConstructor_ = @Inject)\n    20→public class EntityUtils {\n    21→  private final UserModelBuilder userBuilder;\n    22→  private final TagBuilder tagBuilder;\n    23→  private final ArticleModelBuilder articleBuilder;\n    24→  private final CommentBuilder commentBuilder;\n    25→\n    26→  public User user(UserEntity userEntity) {\n    27→    final var id = userEntity.getId();\n    28→    final var username = userEntity.getUsername();\n    29→    final var bio = userEntity.getBio();\n    30→    final var image = userEntity.getImage();\n    31→    final var password = userEntity.getPassword();\n    32→    final var email = userEntity.getEmail();\n    33→    return userBuilder.build(id, username, bio, image, password, email);\n    34→  }\n    35→\n    36→  public Tag tag(TagEntity tagEntity) {\n    37→    return tagBuilder.build(tagEntity.getId(), tagEntity.getName());\n    38→  }\n    39→\n    40→  public Tag tag(TagRelationshipEntity tagRelationshipEntity) {\n    41→    return tag(tagRelationshipEntity.getPrimaryKey().getTag());\n    42→  }\n    43→\n    44→  public Article article(ArticleEntity articleEntity) {\n    45→    return articleBuilder.build(\n    46→        articleEntity.getId(),\n    47→        articleEntity.getSlug(),\n    48→        articleEntity.getTitle(),\n    49→        articleEntity.getDescription(),\n    50→        articleEntity.getBody(),\n    51→        articleEntity.getCreatedAt(),\n    52→        articleEntity.getUpdatedAt(),\n    53→        user(articleEntity.getAuthor()));\n    54→  }\n    55→\n    56→  public Comment comment(CommentEntity commentEntity) {\n    57→    return commentBuilder.build(\n    58→        commentEntity.getId(),\n    59→        user(commentEntity.getAuthor()),\n    60→        article(commentEntity.getArticle()),\n    61→        commentEntity.getBody(),\n    62→        commentEntity.getCreatedAt(),\n    63→        commentEntity.getUpdatedAt());\n    64→  }\n    65→\n    66→  public FavoriteRelationship favoriteRelationship(\n    67→      FavoriteRelationshipEntity favoriteRelationshipEntity) {\n    68→    return new FavoriteRelationship(\n    69→        user(favoriteRelationshipEntity.getUser()),\n    70→        article(favoriteRelationshipEntity.getArticle()));\n    71→  }\n    72→}\n    73→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_015LVkMAFTDHgz1mz9pszJUp","session_id":"4d21e41c-7b8c-412a-ac18-df8336bdf9ca","uuid":"96de9e18-b62e-48bc-bd90-7a3551cdddfc"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01EGXY89Xjxmmy5PU7R6hc3a","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.provider;\n     2→\n     3→import com.github.slugify.Slugify;\n     4→import jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\n     5→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n     6→import lombok.AllArgsConstructor;\n     7→import lombok.NoArgsConstructor;\n     8→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.provider.SlugProvider;\n     9→\n    10→@ApplicationScoped\n    11→@NoArgsConstructor\n    12→@AllArgsConstructor(onConstructor_ = @Inject)\n    13→public class SlugifySlugProvider implements SlugProvider {\n    14→\n    15→  private final Slugify slugify;\n    16→\n    17→  @Override\n    18→  public String slugify(String text) {\n    19→    return slugify.slugify(text);\n    20→  }\n    21→}\n    22→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_015LVkMAFTDHgz1mz9pszJUp","session_id":"4d21e41c-7b8c-412a-ac18-df8336bdf9ca","uuid":"726cbb0e-590a-4429-a793-0950adc2a67d"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01A8VVGdX4iJA7Mw1Zu1T9JX","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.application.web.resource.utils;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\n     4→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n     5→import jakarta.ws.rs.core.SecurityContext;\n     6→import java.security.Principal;\n     7→import java.util.List;\n     8→import java.util.UUID;\n     9→import java.util.stream.Collectors;\n    10→import lombok.AllArgsConstructor;\n    11→import lombok.NoArgsConstructor;\n    12→import org.example.realworldapi.application.web.model.response.*;\n    13→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.*;\n    14→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article.Article;\n    15→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article.PageResult;\n    16→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.comment.Comment;\n    17→\n    18→@ApplicationScoped\n    19→@NoArgsConstructor\n    20→@AllArgsConstructor(onConstructor_ = @Inject)\n    21→public class ResourceUtils {\n    22→\n    23→  private static final int DEFAULT_LIMIT = 20;\n    24→  private final FindUserByUsername findUserByUsername;\n    25→  private final IsFollowingUser isFollowingUser;\n    26→  private final FindArticleTags findArticleTags;\n    27→  private final IsArticleFavorited isArticleFavorited;\n    28→  private final ArticleFavoritesCount articleFavoritesCount;\n    29→\n    30→  public ProfileResponse profileResponse(String username, UUID loggedUserId) {\n    31→    final var user = findUserByUsername.handle(username);\n    32→    final var profileResponse = new ProfileResponse(user);\n    33→    if (loggedUserId != null) {\n    34→      profileResponse.setFollowing(isFollowingUser.handle(loggedUserId, user.getId()));\n    35→    }\n    36→    return profileResponse;\n    37→  }\n    38→\n    39→  public ArticleResponse articleResponse(Article article, UUID loggedUserId) {\n    40→    final var author = article.getAuthor();\n    41→    final var profileResponse = profileResponse(author.getUsername(), author.getId());\n    42→    final var tags = findArticleTags.handle(article);\n    43→    final var favoritesCount = articleFavoritesCount.handle(article.getId());\n    44→    final var articleResponse = new ArticleResponse(article, profileResponse, favoritesCount, tags);\n    45→    if (loggedUserId != null) {\n    46→      articleResponse.setFavorited(isArticleFavorited.handle(article, loggedUserId));\n    47→    }\n    48→    return articleResponse;\n    49→  }\n    50→\n    51→  public ArticlesResponse articlesResponse(PageResult<Article> pageResult, UUID loggedUserId) {\n    52→    final var resultResponse =\n    53→        pageResult.getResult().stream()\n    54→            .map(article -> articleResponse(article, loggedUserId))\n    55→            .collect(Collectors.toList());\n    56→    return new ArticlesResponse(resultResponse, pageResult.getTotal());\n    57→  }\n    58→\n    59→  public CommentResponse commentResponse(Comment comment, UUID loggedUserId) {\n    60→    final var commentAuthor = comment.getAuthor();\n    61→    final var authorResponse = profileResponse(commentAuthor.getUsername(), loggedUserId);\n    62→    return new CommentResponse(comment, authorResponse);\n    63→  }\n    64→\n    65→  public UUID getLoggedUserId(SecurityContext securityContext) {\n    66→    Principal principal = securityContext.getUserPrincipal();\n    67→    return principal != null ? UUID.fromString(principal.getName()) : null;\n    68→  }\n    69→\n    70→  public CommentsResponse commentsResponse(List<Comment> comments, UUID loggedUserId) {\n    71→    final var resultResponse =\n    72→        comments.stream()\n    73→            .map(comment -> commentResponse(comment, loggedUserId))\n    74→            .collect(Collectors.toList());\n    75→    return new CommentsResponse(resultResponse);\n    76→  }\n    77→\n    78→  public int getLimit(int limit) {\n    79→    return limit > 0 ? limit : DEFAULT_LIMIT;\n    80→  }\n    81→}\n    82→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_015LVkMAFTDHgz1mz9pszJUp","session_id":"4d21e41c-7b8c-412a-ac18-df8336bdf9ca","uuid":"6f16d4b5-04b3-468d-9a41-462e17ffeb7d"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01BvSn6oZoq3FkPxYz8rUqJp","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.application.web.resource;\n     2→\n     3→import com.fasterxml.jackson.core.JsonProcessingException;\n     4→import com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.ObjectMapper;\n     5→import jakarta.annotation.security.PermitAll;\n     6→import jakarta.annotation.security.RolesAllowed;\n     7→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n     8→import jakarta.transaction.Transactional;\n     9→import jakarta.validation.Valid;\n    10→import jakarta.validation.constraints.NotBlank;\n    11→import jakarta.validation.constraints.NotNull;\n    12→import jakarta.ws.rs.*;\n    13→import jakarta.ws.rs.core.Context;\n    14→import jakarta.ws.rs.core.MediaType;\n    15→import jakarta.ws.rs.core.Response;\n    16→import jakarta.ws.rs.core.SecurityContext;\n    17→import java.util.List;\n    18→import java.util.UUID;\n    19→import lombok.AllArgsConstructor;\n    20→import lombok.NoArgsConstructor;\n    21→import org.example.realworldapi.application.web.model.request.NewArticleRequest;\n    22→import org.example.realworldapi.application.web.model.request.NewCommentRequest;\n    23→import org.example.realworldapi.application.web.model.request.UpdateArticleRequest;\n    24→import org.example.realworldapi.application.web.resource.utils.ResourceUtils;\n    25→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.*;\n    26→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article.ArticleFilter;\n    27→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.comment.DeleteCommentInput;\n    28→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.constants.ValidationMessages;\n    29→import org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.web.qualifiers.NoWrapRootValueObjectMapper;\n    30→\n    31→@Path(\"/articles\")\n    32→@NoArgsConstructor\n    33→@AllArgsConstructor(onConstructor_ = @Inject)\n    34→public class ArticlesResource {\n    35→\n    36→  private final FindArticlesByFilter findArticlesByFilter;\n    37→  private final CreateArticle createArticle;\n    38→  private final FindMostRecentArticlesByFilter findMostRecentArticlesByFilter;\n    39→  private final FindArticleBySlug findArticleBySlug;\n    40→  private final UpdateArticleBySlug updateArticleBySlug;\n    41→  private final DeleteArticleBySlug deleteArticleBySlug;\n    42→  private final CreateComment createComment;\n    43→  private final DeleteComment deleteComment;\n    44→  private final FindCommentsByArticleSlug findCommentsByArticleSlug;\n    45→  private final FavoriteArticle favoriteArticle;\n    46→  private final UnfavoriteArticle unfavoriteArticle;\n    47→  @NoWrapRootValueObjectMapper ObjectMapper objectMapper;\n    48→  private final ResourceUtils resourceUtils;\n    49→\n    50→  @GET\n    51→  @Path(\"/feed\")\n    52→  @RolesAllowed({\"USER\", \"ADMIN\"})\n    53→  @Produces(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON)\n    54→  public Response feed(\n    55→      @QueryParam(\"offset\") int offset,\n    56→      @QueryParam(\"limit\") int limit,\n    57→      @Context SecurityContext securityContext)\n    58→      throws JsonProcessingException {\n    59→    final var loggedUserId = resourceUtils.getLoggedUserId(securityContext);\n    60→    final var articlesFilter =\n    61→        new ArticleFilter(offset, resourceUtils.getLimit(limit), loggedUserId, null, null, null);\n    62→    final var articlesPageResult = findMostRecentArticlesByFilter.handle(articlesFilter);\n    63→    return Response.ok(\n    64→            objectMapper.writeValueAsString(\n    65→                resourceUtils.articlesResponse(articlesPageResult, loggedUserId)))\n    66→        .status(Response.Status.OK)\n    67→        .build();\n    68→  }\n    69→\n    70→  @GET\n    71→  @Produces(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON)\n    72→  @PermitAll\n    73→  public Response getArticles(\n    74→      @QueryParam(\"offset\") int offset,\n    75→      @QueryParam(\"limit\") int limit,\n    76→      @QueryParam(\"tag\") List<String> tags,\n    77→      @QueryParam(\"author\") List<String> authors,\n    78→      @QueryParam(\"favorited\") List<String> favorited,\n    79→      @Context SecurityContext securityContext)\n    80→      throws JsonProcessingException {\n    81→    final var loggedUserId = resourceUtils.getLoggedUserId(securityContext);\n    82→    final var filter =\n    83→        new ArticleFilter(\n    84→            offset, resourceUtils.getLimit(limit), loggedUserId, tags, authors, favorited);\n    85→    final var articlesPageResult = findArticlesByFilter.handle(filter);\n    86→    return Response.ok(\n    87→            objectMapper.writeValueAsString(\n    88→                resourceUtils.articlesResponse(articlesPageResult, loggedUserId)))\n    89→        .status(Response.Status.OK)\n    90→        .build();\n    91→  }\n    92→\n    93→  @POST\n    94→  @Transactional\n    95→  @RolesAllowed({\"USER\", \"ADMIN\"})\n    96→  @Consumes(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON)\n    97→  @Produces(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON)\n    98→  public Response create(\n    99→      @Valid @NotNull(message = ValidationMessages.REQUEST_BODY_MUST_BE_NOT_NULL)\n   100→          NewArticleRequest newArticleRequest,\n   101→      @Context SecurityContext securityContext) {\n   102→    final var loggedUserId = resourceUtils.getLoggedUserId(securityContext);\n   103→    final var article = createArticle.handle(newArticleRequest.toNewArticleInput(loggedUserId));\n   104→    return Response.ok(resourceUtils.articleResponse(article, loggedUserId))\n   105→        .status(Response.Status.CREATED)\n   106→        .build();\n   107→  }\n   108→\n   109→  @GET\n   110→  @Path(\"/{slug}\")\n   111→  @Produces(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON)\n   112→  public Response findBySlug(\n   113→      @PathParam(\"slug\") @NotBlank(message = ValidationMessages.SLUG_MUST_BE_NOT_BLANK)\n   114→          String slug) {\n   115→    final var article = findArticleBySlug.handle(slug);\n   116→    return Response.ok(resourceUtils.articleResponse(article, null))\n   117→        .status(Response.Status.OK)\n   118→        .build();\n   119→  }\n   120→\n   121→  @PUT\n   122→  @Transactional\n   123→  @Path(\"/{slug}\")\n   124→  @RolesAllowed({\"USER\", \"ADMIN\"})\n   125→  @Consumes(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON)\n   126→  @Produces(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON)\n   127→  public Response update(\n   128→      @PathParam(\"slug\") @NotBlank String slug,\n   129→      @Valid @NotNull UpdateArticleRequest updateArticleRequest,\n   130→      @Context SecurityContext securityContext) {\n   131→    final var loggedUserId = resourceUtils.getLoggedUserId(securityContext);\n   132→    final var updatedArticle =\n   133→        updateArticleBySlug.handle(updateArticleRequest.toUpdateArticleInput(loggedUserId, slug));\n   134→    return Response.ok(resourceUtils.articleResponse(updatedArticle, null))\n   135→        .status(Response.Status.OK)\n   136→        .build();\n   137→  }\n   138→\n   139→  @DELETE\n   140→  @Transactional\n   141→  @Path(\"/{slug}\")\n   142→  @RolesAllowed({\"USER\", \"ADMIN\"})\n   143→  @Produces(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON)\n   144→  public Response delete(\n   145→      @PathParam(\"slug\") @NotBlank(message = ValidationMessages.SLUG_MUST_BE_NOT_BLANK) String slug,\n   146→      @Context SecurityContext securityContext) {\n   147→    final var loggedUserId = resourceUtils.getLoggedUserId(securityContext);\n   148→    deleteArticleBySlug.handle(loggedUserId, slug);\n   149→    return Response.ok().build();\n   150→  }\n   151→\n   152→  @GET\n   153→  @Path(\"/{slug}/comments\")\n   154→  @Produces(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON)\n   155→  public Response getCommentsBySlug(\n   156→      @PathParam(\"slug\") @NotBlank(message = ValidationMessages.SLUG_MUST_BE_NOT_BLANK) String slug,\n   157→      @Context SecurityContext securityContext)\n   158→      throws JsonProcessingException {\n   159→    final var loggedUserId = resourceUtils.getLoggedUserId(securityContext);\n   160→    final var comments = findCommentsByArticleSlug.handle(slug);\n   161→    return Response.ok(\n   162→            objectMapper.writeValueAsString(resourceUtils.commentsResponse(comments, loggedUserId)))\n   163→        .status(Response.Status.OK)\n   164→        .build();\n   165→  }\n   166→\n   167→  @POST\n   168→  @Transactional\n   169→  @Path(\"/{slug}/comments\")\n   170→  @RolesAllowed({\"USER\", \"ADMIN\"})\n   171→  @Consumes(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON)\n   172→  @Produces(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON)\n   173→  public Response createComment(\n   174→      @PathParam(\"slug\") @NotBlank(message = ValidationMessages.SLUG_MUST_BE_NOT_BLANK) String slug,\n   175→      @Valid NewCommentRequest newCommentRequest,\n   176→      @Context SecurityContext securityContext) {\n   177→    final var loggedUserId = resourceUtils.getLoggedUserId(securityContext);\n   178→    final var comment =\n   179→        createComment.handle(newCommentRequest.toNewCommentInput(loggedUserId, slug));\n   180→    return Response.ok(resourceUtils.commentResponse(comment, loggedUserId))\n   181→        .status(Response.Status.OK)\n   182→        .build();\n   183→  }\n   184→\n   185→  @DELETE\n   186→  @Transactional\n   187→  @Path(\"/{slug}/comments/{id}\")\n   188→  @RolesAllowed({\"USER\", \"ADMIN\"})\n   189→  @Produces(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON)\n   190→  public Response deleteComment(\n   191→      @PathParam(\"slug\") @NotBlank(message = ValidationMessages.SLUG_MUST_BE_NOT_BLANK) String slug,\n   192→      @PathParam(\"id\") @NotNull(message = ValidationMessages.COMMENT_ID_MUST_BE_NOT_NULL) UUID id,\n   193→      @Context SecurityContext securityContext) {\n   194→    final var loggedUserId = resourceUtils.getLoggedUserId(securityContext);\n   195→    deleteComment.handle(new DeleteCommentInput(id, loggedUserId, slug));\n   196→    return Response.ok().build();\n   197→  }\n   198→\n   199→  @POST\n   200→  @Transactional\n   201→  @Path(\"/{slug}/favorite\")\n   202→  @RolesAllowed({\"USER\", \"ADMIN\"})\n   203→  @Produces(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON)\n   204→  public Response favoriteArticle(\n   205→      @PathParam(\"slug\") @NotBlank(message = ValidationMessages.SLUG_MUST_BE_NOT_BLANK) String slug,\n   206→      @Context SecurityContext securityContext) {\n   207→    final var loggedUserId = resourceUtils.getLoggedUserId(securityContext);\n   208→    favoriteArticle.handle(slug, loggedUserId);\n   209→    final var article = findArticleBySlug.handle(slug);\n   210→    return Response.ok(resourceUtils.articleResponse(article, loggedUserId))\n   211→        .status(Response.Status.OK)\n   212→        .build();\n   213→  }\n   214→\n   215→  @DELETE\n   216→  @Transactional\n   217→  @Path(\"/{slug}/favorite\")\n   218→  @RolesAllowed({\"USER\", \"ADMIN\"})\n   219→  @Produces(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON)\n   220→  public Response unfavoriteArticle(\n   221→      @PathParam(\"slug\") @NotBlank(message = ValidationMessages.SLUG_MUST_BE_NOT_BLANK) String slug,\n   222→      @Context SecurityContext securityContext) {\n   223→    final var loggedUserId = resourceUtils.getLoggedUserId(securityContext);\n   224→    unfavoriteArticle.handle(slug, loggedUserId);\n   225→    final var article = findArticleBySlug.handle(slug);\n   226→    return Response.ok(resourceUtils.articleResponse(article, loggedUserId))\n   227→        .status(Response.Status.OK)\n   228→        .build();\n   229→  }\n   230→}\n   231→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_015LVkMAFTDHgz1mz9pszJUp","session_id":"4d21e41c-7b8c-412a-ac18-df8336bdf9ca","uuid":"2b06994d-abf9-4347-8980-e16c63ff693c"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01QvaSEqxBvZUdGcJBueuvZf","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.application.web.resource;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n     4→import jakarta.transaction.Transactional;\n     5→import jakarta.validation.Valid;\n     6→import jakarta.validation.constraints.NotNull;\n     7→import jakarta.ws.rs.Consumes;\n     8→import jakarta.ws.rs.NotAuthorizedException;\n     9→import jakarta.ws.rs.POST;\n    10→import jakarta.ws.rs.Path;\n    11→import jakarta.ws.rs.Produces;\n    12→import jakarta.ws.rs.core.MediaType;\n    13→import jakarta.ws.rs.core.Response;\n    14→import lombok.AllArgsConstructor;\n    15→import lombok.NoArgsConstructor;\n    16→import org.example.realworldapi.application.web.model.request.LoginRequest;\n    17→import org.example.realworldapi.application.web.model.request.NewUserRequest;\n    18→import org.example.realworldapi.application.web.model.response.UserResponse;\n    19→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.exception.InvalidPasswordException;\n    20→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.exception.UserNotFoundException;\n    21→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.CreateUser;\n    22→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.LoginUser;\n    23→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.constants.ValidationMessages;\n    24→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.user.User;\n    25→import org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.provider.JwtTokenProvider;\n    26→\n    27→@Path(\"/users\")\n    28→@NoArgsConstructor\n    29→@AllArgsConstructor(onConstructor_ = @Inject)\n    30→public class UsersResource {\n    31→\n    32→  private final CreateUser createUser;\n    33→  private final LoginUser loginUser;\n    34→  @Inject private final JwtTokenProvider tokenProvider;\n    35→\n    36→  @POST\n    37→  @Transactional\n    38→  @Consumes(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON)\n    39→  @Produces(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON)\n    40→  public Response create(\n    41→      @Valid @NotNull(message = ValidationMessages.REQUEST_BODY_MUST_BE_NOT_NULL)\n    42→          NewUserRequest newUserRequest) {\n    43→    final var user = createUser.handle(newUserRequest.toCreateUserInput());\n    44→    final var token = tokenProvider.createUserToken(user.getId().toString());\n    45→    return Response.ok(new UserResponse(user, token)).status(Response.Status.CREATED).build();\n    46→  }\n    47→\n    48→  @POST\n    49→  @Path(\"/login\")\n    50→  @Consumes(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON)\n    51→  @Produces(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON)\n    52→  public Response login(\n    53→      @Valid @NotNull(message = ValidationMessages.REQUEST_BODY_MUST_BE_NOT_NULL)\n    54→          LoginRequest loginRequest) {\n    55→    User user;\n    56→    try {\n    57→      user = loginUser.handle(loginRequest.toLoginUserInput());\n    58→    } catch (UserNotFoundException | InvalidPasswordException ex) {\n    59→      throw new NotAuthorizedException(\"Unauthorized\");\n    60→    }\n    61→    final var token = tokenProvider.createUserToken(user.getId().toString());\n    62→    return Response.ok(new UserResponse(user, token)).status(Response.Status.OK).build();\n    63→  }\n    64→}\n    65→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_015LVkMAFTDHgz1mz9pszJUp","session_id":"4d21e41c-7b8c-412a-ac18-df8336bdf9ca","uuid":"73d2ddb9-1039-4bc8-8008-b66d96b68f95"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01KUBdPtAH25JA1eYPWHnMLD","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.application.web.resource;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.annotation.security.RolesAllowed;\n     4→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n     5→import jakarta.transaction.Transactional;\n     6→import jakarta.validation.Valid;\n     7→import jakarta.validation.constraints.NotNull;\n     8→import jakarta.ws.rs.*;\n     9→import jakarta.ws.rs.core.Context;\n    10→import jakarta.ws.rs.core.MediaType;\n    11→import jakarta.ws.rs.core.Response;\n    12→import jakarta.ws.rs.core.SecurityContext;\n    13→import java.util.UUID;\n    14→import lombok.AllArgsConstructor;\n    15→import lombok.NoArgsConstructor;\n    16→import org.example.realworldapi.application.web.model.request.UpdateUserRequest;\n    17→import org.example.realworldapi.application.web.model.response.UserResponse;\n    18→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.FindUserById;\n    19→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.UpdateUser;\n    20→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.constants.ValidationMessages;\n    21→import org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.provider.JwtTokenProvider;\n    22→\n    23→@Path(\"/user\")\n    24→@NoArgsConstructor\n    25→@AllArgsConstructor(onConstructor_ = @Inject)\n    26→public class UserResource {\n    27→\n    28→  private final FindUserById findUserById;\n    29→  private final UpdateUser updateUser;\n    30→  @Inject JwtTokenProvider tokenProvider;\n    31→\n    32→  @GET\n    33→  @RolesAllowed({\"USER\", \"ADMIN\"})\n    34→  @Produces(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON)\n    35→  public Response getUser(@Context SecurityContext securityContext) {\n    36→    final var userId = UUID.fromString(securityContext.getUserPrincipal().getName());\n    37→    final var user = findUserById.handle(userId);\n    38→    final var token = tokenProvider.createUserToken(user.getId().toString());\n    39→    return Response.ok(new UserResponse(user, token)).status(Response.Status.OK).build();\n    40→  }\n    41→\n    42→  @PUT\n    43→  @Transactional\n    44→  @RolesAllowed({\"USER\", \"ADMIN\"})\n    45→  @Consumes(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON)\n    46→  @Produces(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON)\n    47→  public Response update(\n    48→      @Context SecurityContext securityContext,\n    49→      @Valid @NotNull(message = ValidationMessages.REQUEST_BODY_MUST_BE_NOT_NULL)\n    50→          UpdateUserRequest updateUserRequest) {\n    51→    final var userId = UUID.fromString(securityContext.getUserPrincipal().getName());\n    52→    final var user = updateUser.handle(updateUserRequest.toUpdateUserInput(userId));\n    53→    final var token = tokenProvider.createUserToken(user.getId().toString());\n    54→    return Response.ok(new UserResponse(user, token)).status(Response.Status.OK).build();\n    55→  }\n    56→}\n    57→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_015LVkMAFTDHgz1mz9pszJUp","session_id":"4d21e41c-7b8c-412a-ac18-df8336bdf9ca","uuid":"7d60cc05-9799-488b-8e6f-fbab53f99585"}
