{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_012qFGEytJ31Uz7PZkQPL6H7","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The second Weld initialization (from the servlet Listener) is failing because it's creating a SECOND CDI container, which doesn't know about beans from the first one. The issue is that I have two separate Weld initializations:\n1. `Weld weld = new Weld(); WeldContainer container = weld.initialize();` in Main.java\n2. The `Listener` is initializing another Weld container for the servlet context\n\nThe approach needs to change. I should either:\n1. Use only the Weld SE container and NOT add the Weld Servlet Listener, OR\n2. Use only the Weld Servlet approach\n\nThe correct approach for RESTEasy-CDI with Undertow is simpler - I should use `resteasy-undertow-cdi` which has a `CdiResteasyDeployment` class that handles this automatically. Let me check if that class exists:"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1246,"cache_read_input_tokens":111183,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1246,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":352},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4d21e41c-7b8c-412a-ac18-df8336bdf9ca","uuid":"92f9c89c-bb0e-44eb-9a57-8e770e3c0d34"}
