{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01PhBmpWteeRHbqsynMRPSuK","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The problem is clear: `this.createUser is null` - CDI injection is NOT happening into the JAX-RS resources. RESTEasy is creating resource instances via its own mechanism (POJO construction using the no-arg constructor) instead of getting CDI beans from the container. The `CdiInjectorFactory` isn't working properly.\n\nThe issue is that when `RestApplication.getClasses()` returns resource classes, RESTEasy treats them as POJO resources. With CDI, resources should NOT be listed in `getClasses()` - they should be discovered by CDI automatically. I need to change the approach:\n\n1. Remove resource classes from `RestApplication.getClasses()` \n2. Let CDI + RESTEasy-CDI discover and manage the JAX-RS resources automatically\n3. Make the resources CDI beans with `@RequestScoped` scope"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1986,"cache_read_input_tokens":124385,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1986,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":317},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4d21e41c-7b8c-412a-ac18-df8336bdf9ca","uuid":"b4829349-bcc4-497d-97d2-d80eae10eb18"}
