{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01WVm3h7gD2u1jkMwov8hTuT","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.ws.rs.ApplicationPath;\n     4→import jakarta.ws.rs.core.Application;\n     5→import java.util.HashSet;\n     6→import java.util.Set;\n     7→import org.example.realworldapi.application.web.resource.*;\n     8→import org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.web.mapper.BeanValidationExceptionMapper;\n     9→import org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.web.mapper.ExceptionMappers;\n    10→\n    11→@ApplicationPath(\"/\")\n    12→public class RestApplication extends Application {\n    13→\n    14→    @Override\n    15→    public Set<Class<?>> getClasses() {\n    16→        Set<Class<?>> classes = new HashSet<>();\n    17→        // Resources\n    18→        classes.add(ArticlesResource.class);\n    19→        classes.add(UsersResource.class);\n    20→        classes.add(UserResource.class);\n    21→        classes.add(ProfilesResource.class);\n    22→        classes.add(TagsResource.class);\n    23→        // Exception mappers\n    24→        classes.add(BeanValidationExceptionMapper.class);\n    25→        classes.add(ExceptionMappers.class);\n    26→        // Security filters\n    27→        classes.add(SecurityFilter.class);\n    28→        classes.add(RolesAllowedFilter.class);\n    29→        return classes;\n    30→    }\n    31→}\n    32→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4d21e41c-7b8c-412a-ac18-df8336bdf9ca","uuid":"8e33228a-ae92-460e-82e3-bdac4d336d78"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_019euPXTJeGQ55EQdqR7SQso","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The problem is RESTEasy-CDI integration. When `getClasses()` returns resource classes, RESTEasy uses POJO instantiation. For CDI-managed resources, I should NOT override `getClasses()`. Instead, I should let RESTEasy-CDI scan for `@Path`-annotated CDI beans. But the providers (exception mappers, filters) still need to be registered.\n\nActually, the proper approach with RESTEasy-CDI is to add `@RequestScoped` to the resource classes and return an empty set from `getClasses()`, or better yet, not override it at all. But we need the providers registered. Let me use a different approach - register resources as `getSingletons()` from CDI, or better yet, just don't override `getClasses()` and add `@RequestScoped` to resources:"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1148,"cache_read_input_tokens":126371,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1148,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":421},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4d21e41c-7b8c-412a-ac18-df8336bdf9ca","uuid":"f49846ac-6bce-4fe1-8a80-0b0ada3ce034"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_019euPXTJeGQ55EQdqR7SQso","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_bdrk_01G5K2VrY7vhnyoJHBt64hf9","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__realworld__quarkus__jakarta/run_1/output/src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/RestApplication.java","content":"package org.example.realworldapi;\n\nimport jakarta.ws.rs.ApplicationPath;\nimport jakarta.ws.rs.core.Application;\n\n@ApplicationPath(\"/\")\npublic class RestApplication extends Application {\n    // Let RESTEasy-CDI discover @Path resources and @Provider classes automatically\n    // Do NOT override getClasses() - that would cause POJO instantiation instead of CDI\n}\n"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1148,"cache_read_input_tokens":126371,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1148,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":421},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4d21e41c-7b8c-412a-ac18-df8336bdf9ca","uuid":"b6a03594-4e70-4e78-8824-8fedd7cfc486"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01G5K2VrY7vhnyoJHBt64hf9","type":"tool_result","content":"The file /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__realworld__quarkus__jakarta/run_1/output/src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/RestApplication.java has been updated. Here's the result of running `cat -n` on a snippet of the edited file:\n     1→package org.example.realworldapi;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.ws.rs.ApplicationPath;\n     4→import jakarta.ws.rs.core.Application;\n     5→\n     6→@ApplicationPath(\"/\")\n     7→public class RestApplication extends Application {\n     8→    // Let RESTEasy-CDI discover @Path resources and @Provider classes automatically\n     9→    // Do NOT override getClasses() - that would cause POJO instantiation instead of CDI\n    10→}\n    11→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4d21e41c-7b8c-412a-ac18-df8336bdf9ca","uuid":"e8f3b51c-57dd-48d5-ab55-560c1cf238f6"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01UMCSAaVDxmwPyQ1py2msgw","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now I need to make sure all JAX-RS resources have `@RequestScoped` annotation for CDI to recognize them, and all providers/filters have `@Provider` annotation. Let me also add `@RequestScoped` to the resource classes:"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":653,"cache_read_input_tokens":127519,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":653,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":624},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4d21e41c-7b8c-412a-ac18-df8336bdf9ca","uuid":"1f1a04a1-e15a-48e4-9911-a01e25fd0392"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01UMCSAaVDxmwPyQ1py2msgw","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_bdrk_01UeArWwQQb6WxcnhUxSDxYj","name":"Task","input":{"description":"Add @RequestScoped to JAX-RS resources","subagent_type":"general-purpose","prompt":"I need to add CDI scope annotations to JAX-RS resource classes so that RESTEasy-CDI can discover and manage them properly. \n\nThe base directory is: /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__realworld__quarkus__jakarta/run_1/output/src/main/java\n\nFor these 5 JAX-RS resource files, add `@RequestScoped` annotation and `import jakarta.enterprise.context.RequestScoped;`:\n\n1. org/example/realworldapi/application/web/resource/ArticlesResource.java\n2. org/example/realworldapi/application/web/resource/UsersResource.java\n3. org/example/realworldapi/application/web/resource/UserResource.java\n4. org/example/realworldapi/application/web/resource/ProfilesResource.java\n5. org/example/realworldapi/application/web/resource/TagsResource.java\n\nFor each file:\n1. Read the file\n2. Add `import jakarta.enterprise.context.RequestScoped;` to the imports\n3. Add `@RequestScoped` annotation right before `@Path(...)` annotation\n4. The order should be: @RequestScoped, @NoArgsConstructor, @AllArgsConstructor, @Path\n\nAlso check these filter/provider/mapper files and make sure they have `@Provider` annotation (they should already):\n- org/example/realworldapi/SecurityFilter.java\n- org/example/realworldapi/RolesAllowedFilter.java\n- org/example/realworldapi/infrastructure/web/mapper/BeanValidationExceptionMapper.java\n- org/example/realworldapi/infrastructure/web/mapper/ExceptionMappers.java\n\nFor SecurityFilter.java and RolesAllowedFilter.java, also check if they are in the right place and have proper annotations for CDI discovery.\n\nReport which files were modified."}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":653,"cache_read_input_tokens":127519,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":653,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":624},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4d21e41c-7b8c-412a-ac18-df8336bdf9ca","uuid":"b726f945-0a35-4bc8-81e5-b2f733ce4a25"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I need to add CDI scope annotations to JAX-RS resource classes so that RESTEasy-CDI can discover and manage them properly. \n\nThe base directory is: /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__realworld__quarkus__jakarta/run_1/output/src/main/java\n\nFor these 5 JAX-RS resource files, add `@RequestScoped` annotation and `import jakarta.enterprise.context.RequestScoped;`:\n\n1. org/example/realworldapi/application/web/resource/ArticlesResource.java\n2. org/example/realworldapi/application/web/resource/UsersResource.java\n3. org/example/realworldapi/application/web/resource/UserResource.java\n4. org/example/realworldapi/application/web/resource/ProfilesResource.java\n5. org/example/realworldapi/application/web/resource/TagsResource.java\n\nFor each file:\n1. Read the file\n2. Add `import jakarta.enterprise.context.RequestScoped;` to the imports\n3. Add `@RequestScoped` annotation right before `@Path(...)` annotation\n4. The order should be: @RequestScoped, @NoArgsConstructor, @AllArgsConstructor, @Path\n\nAlso check these filter/provider/mapper files and make sure they have `@Provider` annotation (they should already):\n- org/example/realworldapi/SecurityFilter.java\n- org/example/realworldapi/RolesAllowedFilter.java\n- org/example/realworldapi/infrastructure/web/mapper/BeanValidationExceptionMapper.java\n- org/example/realworldapi/infrastructure/web/mapper/ExceptionMappers.java\n\nFor SecurityFilter.java and RolesAllowedFilter.java, also check if they are in the right place and have proper annotations for CDI discovery.\n\nReport which files were modified."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01UeArWwQQb6WxcnhUxSDxYj","session_id":"4d21e41c-7b8c-412a-ac18-df8336bdf9ca","uuid":"fa1dd5d3-c41d-4287-a5e2-20b98a736093"}
