{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-5-20250929","id":"msg_bdrk_01XwsUhF4X1AkhXQ5iNioEXQ","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_bdrk_01VErQgdKvKoX7WAmUEPy8n6","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__realworld__quarkus__jakarta/run_1/output/src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/infrastructure/web/mapper/ExceptionMappers.java"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":6,"cache_creation_input_tokens":8030,"cache_read_input_tokens":11798,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":8030,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":460},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01UeArWwQQb6WxcnhUxSDxYj","session_id":"4d21e41c-7b8c-412a-ac18-df8336bdf9ca","uuid":"64722086-d927-4a66-b56b-01be0178206f"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01NWxnAxNoSPkvfWWR2kQEjG","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi;\n     2→\n     3→import com.nimbusds.jose.JWSVerifier;\n     4→import com.nimbusds.jose.crypto.RSASSAVerifier;\n     5→import com.nimbusds.jwt.JWTClaimsSet;\n     6→import com.nimbusds.jwt.SignedJWT;\n     7→import jakarta.annotation.Priority;\n     8→import jakarta.ws.rs.Priorities;\n     9→import jakarta.ws.rs.container.ContainerRequestContext;\n    10→import jakarta.ws.rs.container.ContainerRequestFilter;\n    11→import jakarta.ws.rs.ext.Provider;\n    12→import java.io.InputStream;\n    13→import java.security.KeyFactory;\n    14→import java.security.PublicKey;\n    15→import java.security.interfaces.RSAPublicKey;\n    16→import java.security.spec.X509EncodedKeySpec;\n    17→import java.util.*;\n    18→\n    19→@Provider\n    20→@Priority(Priorities.AUTHENTICATION)\n    21→public class SecurityFilter implements ContainerRequestFilter {\n    22→\n    23→    private RSAPublicKey publicKey;\n    24→\n    25→    public SecurityFilter() {\n    26→        try {\n    27→            publicKey = loadPublicKey();\n    28→        } catch (Exception e) {\n    29→            throw new RuntimeException(\"Failed to load public key\", e);\n    30→        }\n    31→    }\n    32→\n    33→    private RSAPublicKey loadPublicKey() throws Exception {\n    34→        try (InputStream is = Thread.currentThread().getContextClassLoader()\n    35→                .getResourceAsStream(\"publicKey.pem\")) {\n    36→            if (is == null) {\n    37→                throw new RuntimeException(\"publicKey.pem not found on classpath\");\n    38→            }\n    39→            String pem = new String(is.readAllBytes());\n    40→            pem = pem.replace(\"-----BEGIN PUBLIC KEY-----\", \"\")\n    41→                      .replace(\"-----END PUBLIC KEY-----\", \"\")\n    42→                      .replaceAll(\"\\\\s\", \"\");\n    43→            byte[] decoded = Base64.getDecoder().decode(pem);\n    44→            X509EncodedKeySpec spec = new X509EncodedKeySpec(decoded);\n    45→            KeyFactory kf = KeyFactory.getInstance(\"RSA\");\n    46→            return (RSAPublicKey) kf.generatePublic(spec);\n    47→        }\n    48→    }\n    49→\n    50→    @Override\n    51→    public void filter(ContainerRequestContext requestContext) {\n    52→        String authHeader = requestContext.getHeaderString(\"Authorization\");\n    53→        if (authHeader != null && authHeader.startsWith(\"Bearer \")) {\n    54→            String token = authHeader.substring(7).trim();\n    55→            try {\n    56→                SignedJWT signedJWT = SignedJWT.parse(token);\n    57→                JWSVerifier verifier = new RSASSAVerifier(publicKey);\n    58→                if (signedJWT.verify(verifier)) {\n    59→                    JWTClaimsSet claims = signedJWT.getJWTClaimsSet();\n    60→                    String subject = claims.getSubject();\n    61→                    List<String> groups = claims.getStringListClaim(\"groups\");\n    62→                    if (groups == null) {\n    63→                        groups = List.of(\"USER\");\n    64→                    }\n    65→                    final String sub = subject;\n    66→                    final Set<String> roles = new HashSet<>(groups);\n    67→                    requestContext.setSecurityContext(new jakarta.ws.rs.core.SecurityContext() {\n    68→                        @Override\n    69→                        public java.security.Principal getUserPrincipal() {\n    70→                            return () -> sub;\n    71→                        }\n    72→                        @Override\n    73→                        public boolean isUserInRole(String role) {\n    74→                            return roles.contains(role);\n    75→                        }\n    76→                        @Override\n    77→                        public boolean isSecure() {\n    78→                            return false;\n    79→                        }\n    80→                        @Override\n    81→                        public String getAuthenticationScheme() {\n    82→                            return \"Bearer\";\n    83→                        }\n    84→                    });\n    85→                }\n    86→            } catch (Exception e) {\n    87→                // Invalid token - proceed without authentication\n    88→            }\n    89→        }\n    90→    }\n    91→}\n    92→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01UeArWwQQb6WxcnhUxSDxYj","session_id":"4d21e41c-7b8c-412a-ac18-df8336bdf9ca","uuid":"16329395-903c-429d-b45b-c81513ca82a5"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Q8KvXFx3baaignHbNbEayj","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.annotation.Priority;\n     4→import jakarta.annotation.security.PermitAll;\n     5→import jakarta.annotation.security.RolesAllowed;\n     6→import jakarta.ws.rs.NotAuthorizedException;\n     7→import jakarta.ws.rs.ForbiddenException;\n     8→import jakarta.ws.rs.Priorities;\n     9→import jakarta.ws.rs.container.ContainerRequestContext;\n    10→import jakarta.ws.rs.container.ContainerRequestFilter;\n    11→import jakarta.ws.rs.container.ResourceInfo;\n    12→import jakarta.ws.rs.core.Context;\n    13→import jakarta.ws.rs.ext.Provider;\n    14→import java.lang.reflect.Method;\n    15→\n    16→@Provider\n    17→@Priority(Priorities.AUTHORIZATION)\n    18→public class RolesAllowedFilter implements ContainerRequestFilter {\n    19→\n    20→    @Context\n    21→    private ResourceInfo resourceInfo;\n    22→\n    23→    @Override\n    24→    public void filter(ContainerRequestContext requestContext) {\n    25→        Method method = resourceInfo.getResourceMethod();\n    26→        if (method == null) return;\n    27→\n    28→        // Check for @PermitAll - allow all\n    29→        if (method.isAnnotationPresent(PermitAll.class)) {\n    30→            return;\n    31→        }\n    32→\n    33→        // Check for @RolesAllowed\n    34→        RolesAllowed rolesAllowed = method.getAnnotation(RolesAllowed.class);\n    35→        if (rolesAllowed == null) {\n    36→            // Check class level\n    37→            rolesAllowed = resourceInfo.getResourceClass().getAnnotation(RolesAllowed.class);\n    38→        }\n    39→\n    40→        if (rolesAllowed == null) {\n    41→            // No security annotation - allow\n    42→            return;\n    43→        }\n    44→\n    45→        // Require authentication\n    46→        if (requestContext.getSecurityContext().getUserPrincipal() == null) {\n    47→            throw new NotAuthorizedException(\"Bearer\");\n    48→        }\n    49→\n    50→        // Check roles\n    51→        String[] roles = rolesAllowed.value();\n    52→        for (String role : roles) {\n    53→            if (requestContext.getSecurityContext().isUserInRole(role)) {\n    54→                return;\n    55→            }\n    56→        }\n    57→\n    58→        throw new ForbiddenException(\"Insufficient permissions\");\n    59→    }\n    60→}\n    61→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01UeArWwQQb6WxcnhUxSDxYj","session_id":"4d21e41c-7b8c-412a-ac18-df8336bdf9ca","uuid":"98749a52-47e0-4200-8950-70cfb299fb36"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Cqk6RzNDtZiBM2Zj2svA8e","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.web.mapper;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.validation.ConstraintViolationException;\n     4→import jakarta.ws.rs.core.Response;\n     5→import jakarta.ws.rs.ext.ExceptionMapper;\n     6→import jakarta.ws.rs.ext.Provider;\n     7→import org.example.realworldapi.application.web.model.response.ErrorResponse;\n     8→\n     9→@Provider\n    10→public class BeanValidationExceptionMapper\n    11→    implements ExceptionMapper<ConstraintViolationException> {\n    12→\n    13→  @Override\n    14→  public Response toResponse(ConstraintViolationException e) {\n    15→\n    16→    ErrorResponse errorResponse = new ErrorResponse();\n    17→\n    18→    e.getConstraintViolations()\n    19→        .iterator()\n    20→        .forEachRemaining(constraint -> errorResponse.getBody().add(constraint.getMessage()));\n    21→\n    22→    return Response.ok(errorResponse).status(422).build();\n    23→  }\n    24→}\n    25→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01UeArWwQQb6WxcnhUxSDxYj","session_id":"4d21e41c-7b8c-412a-ac18-df8336bdf9ca","uuid":"1183d971-0fbc-4c9d-80db-423386da64b8"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01VErQgdKvKoX7WAmUEPy8n6","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.web.mapper;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.ws.rs.ForbiddenException;\n     4→import jakarta.ws.rs.NotAuthorizedException;\n     5→import jakarta.ws.rs.core.Response;\n     6→import jakarta.ws.rs.ext.ExceptionMapper;\n     7→import jakarta.ws.rs.ext.Provider;\n     8→import org.example.realworldapi.application.web.model.response.ErrorResponse;\n     9→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.exception.*;\n    10→\n    11→@Provider\n    12→public class ExceptionMappers implements ExceptionMapper<RuntimeException> {\n    13→\n    14→  @Override\n    15→  public Response toResponse(RuntimeException e) {\n    16→    if (e instanceof NotAuthorizedException) {\n    17→      return Response.status(Response.Status.UNAUTHORIZED)\n    18→          .entity(new ErrorResponse(\"Unauthorized\"))\n    19→          .build();\n    20→    }\n    21→    if (e instanceof ForbiddenException) {\n    22→      return Response.status(Response.Status.FORBIDDEN)\n    23→          .entity(new ErrorResponse(\"Forbidden\"))\n    24→          .build();\n    25→    }\n    26→    if (e instanceof EmailAlreadyExistsException) {\n    27→      return Response.status(Response.Status.CONFLICT)\n    28→          .entity(new ErrorResponse(e.getMessage()))\n    29→          .build();\n    30→    }\n    31→    if (e instanceof UsernameAlreadyExistsException) {\n    32→      return Response.status(Response.Status.CONFLICT)\n    33→          .entity(new ErrorResponse(e.getMessage()))\n    34→          .build();\n    35→    }\n    36→    if (e instanceof UserNotFoundException) {\n    37→      return Response.status(Response.Status.NOT_FOUND)\n    38→          .entity(new ErrorResponse(e.getMessage()))\n    39→          .build();\n    40→    }\n    41→    if (e instanceof InvalidPasswordException) {\n    42→      return Response.status(Response.Status.UNAUTHORIZED)\n    43→          .entity(new ErrorResponse(e.getMessage()))\n    44→          .build();\n    45→    }\n    46→    if (e instanceof TagNotFoundException) {\n    47→      return Response.status(Response.Status.NOT_FOUND)\n    48→          .entity(new ErrorResponse(e.getMessage()))\n    49→          .build();\n    50→    }\n    51→    if (e instanceof ArticleNotFoundException) {\n    52→      return Response.status(Response.Status.NOT_FOUND)\n    53→          .entity(new ErrorResponse(e.getMessage()))\n    54→          .build();\n    55→    }\n    56→    if (e instanceof ModelValidationException) {\n    57→      return Response.status(422)\n    58→          .entity(new ErrorResponse(e.getMessage()))\n    59→          .build();\n    60→    }\n    61→    // Default - internal server error\n    62→    return Response.status(Response.Status.INTERNAL_SERVER_ERROR)\n    63→        .entity(new ErrorResponse(e.getMessage() != null ? e.getMessage() : \"Internal Server Error\"))\n    64→        .build();\n    65→  }\n    66→}\n    67→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01UeArWwQQb6WxcnhUxSDxYj","session_id":"4d21e41c-7b8c-412a-ac18-df8336bdf9ca","uuid":"04b19fa9-4703-44f3-88a6-2848aa9f31bf"}
