{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_015P2HPqE4QQoMgcGu5KjN9A","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"`WELD-000810: Cannot place qualifiers on final fields`. The issue is that with `@AllArgsConstructor(onConstructor_ = @Inject)`, Lombok also generates `@Inject` on the fields when `onConstructor_` is used... wait, no. The issue is that the `final` fields plus `@NoArgsConstructor(force = true)` - Weld sees the constructor injection via `@Inject` on the all-args constructor AND the fields are `final`, which is causing confusion.\n\nThe real solution: I need to change the approach entirely. Instead of `@AllArgsConstructor(onConstructor_ = @Inject)` with `final` fields, I should use **field injection** (non-final fields with `@Inject`). This is the simplest approach for Weld CDI with JAX-RS resources:"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":735,"cache_read_input_tokens":145707,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":735,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":680},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4d21e41c-7b8c-412a-ac18-df8336bdf9ca","uuid":"30b10959-1fc6-42e5-a5f6-5e2e03ef6154"}
