{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_018FhkZ2L2X3op9oU52DREsf","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.repository.hibernate.entity;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\n     4→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n     5→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article.Article;\n     6→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article.ArticleModelBuilder;\n     7→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article.FavoriteRelationship;\n     8→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.comment.Comment;\n     9→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.comment.CommentBuilder;\n    10→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.tag.Tag;\n    11→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.tag.TagBuilder;\n    12→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.user.User;\n    13→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.user.UserModelBuilder;\n    14→\n    15→@ApplicationScoped\n    16→public class EntityUtils {\n    17→  @Inject private UserModelBuilder userBuilder;\n    18→  @Inject private TagBuilder tagBuilder;\n    19→  @Inject private ArticleModelBuilder articleBuilder;\n    20→  @Inject private CommentBuilder commentBuilder;\n    21→\n    22→  public User user(UserEntity userEntity) {\n    23→    final var id = userEntity.getId();\n    24→    final var username = userEntity.getUsername();\n    25→    final var bio = userEntity.getBio();\n    26→    final var image = userEntity.getImage();\n    27→    final var password = userEntity.getPassword();\n    28→    final var email = userEntity.getEmail();\n    29→    return userBuilder.build(id, username, bio, image, password, email);\n    30→  }\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01WpA5rct3PmoAakFYjyGxkK","session_id":"4d21e41c-7b8c-412a-ac18-df8336bdf9ca","uuid":"807d88e0-33ad-4afc-a7ac-631bd58c45b8"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01WpA5rct3PmoAakFYjyGxkK","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! All transformations have been completed successfully. Let me create a summary of all the changes made.\n\n## Summary of CDI Field Injection Conversion\n\nI have successfully converted all 8 CDI-managed classes from Lombok constructor injection to plain CDI field injection. This resolves the Weld CDI issue \"WELD-000810: Cannot place qualifiers on final fields\" that occurs with the combination of `@AllArgsConstructor(onConstructor_ = @Inject)` and `@NoArgsConstructor(force = true)` on `final` fields.\n\n### Files Modified\n\nAll files are located under: `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__realworld__quarkus__jakarta/run_1/output/src/main/java/`\n\n#### 1. **ArticlesResource.java**\n- **Removed**: `@NoArgsConstructor(force = true)`, `@AllArgsConstructor(onConstructor_ = @Inject)`\n- **Removed imports**: `lombok.AllArgsConstructor`, `lombok.NoArgsConstructor`\n- **Converted 12 fields** from `private final` to `@Inject private`:\n  - `FindArticlesByFilter findArticlesByFilter`\n  - `CreateArticle createArticle`\n  - `FindMostRecentArticlesByFilter findMostRecentArticlesByFilter`\n  - `FindArticleBySlug findArticleBySlug`\n  - `UpdateArticleBySlug updateArticleBySlug`\n  - `DeleteArticleBySlug deleteArticleBySlug`\n  - `CreateComment createComment`\n  - `DeleteComment deleteComment`\n  - `FindCommentsByArticleSlug findCommentsByArticleSlug`\n  - `FavoriteArticle favoriteArticle`\n  - `UnfavoriteArticle unfavoriteArticle`\n  - `ResourceUtils resourceUtils`\n- **Special case**: `objectMapper` with `@NoWrapRootValueObjectMapper` qualifier became `@Inject @NoWrapRootValueObjectMapper private ObjectMapper objectMapper`\n\n#### 2. **UsersResource.java**\n- **Removed**: `@NoArgsConstructor(force = true)`, `@AllArgsConstructor(onConstructor_ = @Inject)`\n- **Removed imports**: `lombok.AllArgsConstructor`, `lombok.NoArgsConstructor`\n- **Converted 3 fields** from `private final` to `@Inject private`:\n  - `CreateUser createUser`\n  - `LoginUser loginUser`\n  - `JwtTokenProvider tokenProvider` (already had `@Inject`, removed duplicate and `final`)\n\n#### 3. **UserResource.java**\n- **Removed**: `@NoArgsConstructor(force = true)`, `@AllArgsConstructor(onConstructor_ = @Inject)`\n- **Removed imports**: `lombok.AllArgsConstructor`, `lombok.NoArgsConstructor`\n- **Converted 3 fields** to `@Inject private`:\n  - `FindUserById findUserById`\n  - `UpdateUser updateUser`\n  - `JwtTokenProvider tokenProvider` (already had `@Inject`, added `private` modifier)\n\n#### 4. **ProfilesResource.java**\n- **Removed**: `@NoArgsConstructor(force = true)`, `@AllArgsConstructor(onConstructor_ = @Inject)`\n- **Removed imports**: `lombok.AllArgsConstructor`, `lombok.NoArgsConstructor`\n- **Converted 3 fields** from `private final` to `@Inject private`:\n  - `FollowUserByUsername followUserByUsername`\n  - `UnfollowUserByUsername unfollowUserByUsername`\n  - `ResourceUtils resourceUtils`\n\n#### 5. **TagsResource.java**\n- **Removed**: `@NoArgsConstructor(force = true)`, `@AllArgsConstructor(onConstructor_ = @Inject)`\n- **Removed imports**: `lombok.AllArgsConstructor`, `lombok.NoArgsConstructor`\n- **Converted 2 fields**:\n  - `objectMapper` with `@NoWrapRootValueObjectMapper` qualifier became `@Inject @NoWrapRootValueObjectMapper private ObjectMapper objectMapper`\n  - `FindTags findTags` became `@Inject private FindTags findTags`\n\n#### 6. **ResourceUtils.java**\n- **Removed**: `@NoArgsConstructor(force = true)`, `@AllArgsConstructor(onConstructor_ = @Inject)`\n- **Removed imports**: `lombok.AllArgsConstructor`, `lombok.NoArgsConstructor`\n- **Converted 5 fields** from `private final` to `@Inject private`:\n  - `FindUserByUsername findUserByUsername`\n  - `IsFollowingUser isFollowingUser`\n  - `FindArticleTags findArticleTags`\n  - `IsArticleFavorited isArticleFavorited`\n  - `ArticleFavoritesCount articleFavoritesCount`\n\n#### 7. **EntityUtils.java**\n- **Removed**: `@NoArgsConstructor(force = true)`, `@AllArgsConstructor(onConstructor_ = @Inject)`\n- **Removed imports**: `lombok.AllArgsConstructor`, `lombok.NoArgsConstructor`\n- **Converted 4 fields** from `private final` to `@Inject private`:\n  - `UserModelBuilder userBuilder`\n  - `TagBuilder tagBuilder`\n  - `ArticleModelBuilder articleBuilder`\n  - `CommentBuilder commentBuilder`\n\n#### 8. **SlugifySlugProvider.java**\n- **Removed**: `@NoArgsConstructor(force = true)`, `@AllArgsConstructor(onConstructor_ = @Inject)`\n- **Removed imports**: `lombok.AllArgsConstructor`, `lombok.NoArgsConstructor`\n- **Converted 1 field** from `private final` to `@Inject private`:\n  - `Slugify slugify`\n\n### Key Changes Applied\n\n1. **Removed Lombok annotations**: `@AllArgsConstructor(onConstructor_ = @Inject)` and `@NoArgsConstructor(force = true)`\n2. **Removed Lombok imports**: No longer importing `lombok.AllArgsConstructor` or `lombok.NoArgsConstructor`\n3. **Changed all dependency fields**: From `private final SomeType fieldName` to `@Inject private SomeType fieldName`\n4. **Preserved CDI qualifiers**: Fields with qualifiers like `@NoWrapRootValueObjectMapper` now have both `@Inject` and the qualifier (e.g., `@Inject @NoWrapRootValueObjectMapper private ObjectMapper objectMapper`)\n5. **Retained jakarta.inject.Inject import**: All files already had this import, which is now actively used\n\nThis transformation ensures compatibility with Weld CDI while maintaining all dependency injection functionality. The change from constructor injection to field injection eliminates the issue with final fields and CDI qualifiers."}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4d21e41c-7b8c-412a-ac18-df8336bdf9ca","uuid":"39d10976-cc17-432e-a703-5aadd5f341a0"}
