{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01GXp7zg1bT9ARNiXzt7Fsn9","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The issue is clear - there are no `RESTEASY002220: Adding class resource` log lines, meaning no resources are being discovered. The `RestApplication` is being deployed but RESTEasy doesn't find the `@Path` resource classes. This is because the empty `RestApplication` with CDI scanning requires the Weld servlet environment to be properly initialized BEFORE RESTEasy scans.\n\nI see `WELD-ENV-001007: Initialize Weld using ServletContextListener` - the Weld servlet listener is starting a *second* Weld instance during the servlet context init. This is the dual-Weld problem. The CdiInjectorFactory might be using this second (incomplete) container.\n\nLet me check the resource classes and the Main.java to figure out the right approach. The issue is that RESTEasy's CDI scanning via `CdiInjectorFactory` + empty `Application` doesn't automatically discover `@Path` beans. We need to either:\n1. Explicitly register resource classes in the deployment\n2. Or use the RESTEasy scanning mechanism"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":3014,"cache_read_input_tokens":32102,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":3014,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":428},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4d21e41c-7b8c-412a-ac18-df8336bdf9ca","uuid":"1c6f25d4-6999-4aae-9bf4-232b291c36a6"}
