{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_015ge7UUv1wTHf8p4G78Kw68","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.application.web.resource;\n     2→\n     3→import com.fasterxml.jackson.core.JsonProcessingException;\n     4→import com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.ObjectMapper;\n     5→import jakarta.annotation.security.PermitAll;\n     6→import jakarta.annotation.security.RolesAllowed;\n     7→import jakarta.enterprise.context.RequestScoped;\n     8→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n     9→import jakarta.transaction.Transactional;\n    10→import jakarta.validation.Valid;\n    11→import jakarta.validation.constraints.NotBlank;\n    12→import jakarta.validation.constraints.NotNull;\n    13→import jakarta.ws.rs.*;\n    14→import jakarta.ws.rs.core.Context;\n    15→import jakarta.ws.rs.core.MediaType;\n    16→import jakarta.ws.rs.core.Response;\n    17→import jakarta.ws.rs.core.SecurityContext;\n    18→import java.util.List;\n    19→import java.util.UUID;\n    20→import org.example.realworldapi.application.web.model.request.NewArticleRequest;\n    21→import org.example.realworldapi.application.web.model.request.NewCommentRequest;\n    22→import org.example.realworldapi.application.web.model.request.UpdateArticleRequest;\n    23→import org.example.realworldapi.application.web.resource.utils.ResourceUtils;\n    24→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.*;\n    25→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article.ArticleFilter;\n    26→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.comment.DeleteCommentInput;\n    27→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.constants.ValidationMessages;\n    28→import org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.web.qualifiers.NoWrapRootValueObjectMapper;\n    29→\n    30→@RequestScoped\n    31→@Path(\"/articles\")\n    32→public class ArticlesResource {\n    33→\n    34→  @Inject private FindArticlesByFilter findArticlesByFilter;\n    35→  @Inject private CreateArticle createArticle;\n    36→  @Inject private FindMostRecentArticlesByFilter findMostRecentArticlesByFilter;\n    37→  @Inject private FindArticleBySlug findArticleBySlug;\n    38→  @Inject private UpdateArticleBySlug updateArticleBySlug;\n    39→  @Inject private DeleteArticleBySlug deleteArticleBySlug;\n    40→  @Inject private CreateComment createComment;\n    41→  @Inject private DeleteComment deleteComment;\n    42→  @Inject private FindCommentsByArticleSlug findCommentsByArticleSlug;\n    43→  @Inject private FavoriteArticle favoriteArticle;\n    44→  @Inject private UnfavoriteArticle unfavoriteArticle;\n    45→  @Inject @NoWrapRootValueObjectMapper private ObjectMapper objectMapper;\n    46→  @Inject private ResourceUtils resourceUtils;\n    47→\n    48→  @GET\n    49→  @Path(\"/feed\")\n    50→  @RolesAllowed({\"USER\", \"ADMIN\"})\n    51→  @Produces(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON)\n    52→  public Response feed(\n    53→      @QueryParam(\"offset\") int offset,\n    54→      @QueryParam(\"limit\") int limit,\n    55→      @Context SecurityContext securityContext)\n    56→      throws JsonProcessingException {\n    57→    final var loggedUserId = resourceUtils.getLoggedUserId(securityContext);\n    58→    final var articlesFilter =\n    59→        new ArticleFilter(offset, resourceUtils.getLimit(limit), loggedUserId, null, null, null);\n    60→    final var articlesPageResult = findMostRecentArticlesByFilter.handle(articlesFilter);\n    61→    return Response.ok(\n    62→            objectMapper.writeValueAsString(\n    63→                resourceUtils.articlesResponse(articlesPageResult, loggedUserId)))\n    64→        .status(Response.Status.OK)\n    65→        .build();\n    66→  }\n    67→\n    68→  @GET\n    69→  @Produces(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON)\n    70→  @PermitAll\n    71→  public Response getArticles(\n    72→      @QueryParam(\"offset\") int offset,\n    73→      @QueryParam(\"limit\") int limit,\n    74→      @QueryParam(\"tag\") List<String> tags,\n    75→      @QueryParam(\"author\") List<String> authors,\n    76→      @QueryParam(\"favorited\") List<String> favorited,\n    77→      @Context SecurityContext securityContext)\n    78→      throws JsonProcessingException {\n    79→    final var loggedUserId = resourceUtils.getLoggedUserId(securityContext);\n    80→    final var filter =\n    81→        new ArticleFilter(\n    82→            offset, resourceUtils.getLimit(limit), loggedUserId, tags, authors, favorited);\n    83→    final var articlesPageResult = findArticlesByFilter.handle(filter);\n    84→    return Response.ok(\n    85→            objectMapper.writeValueAsString(\n    86→                resourceUtils.articlesResponse(articlesPageResult, loggedUserId)))\n    87→        .status(Response.Status.OK)\n    88→        .build();\n    89→  }\n    90→\n    91→  @POST\n    92→  @Transactional\n    93→  @RolesAllowed({\"USER\", \"ADMIN\"})\n    94→  @Consumes(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON)\n    95→  @Produces(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON)\n    96→  public Response create(\n    97→      @Valid @NotNull(message = ValidationMessages.REQUEST_BODY_MUST_BE_NOT_NULL)\n    98→          NewArticleRequest newArticleRequest,\n    99→      @Context SecurityContext securityContext) {\n   100→    final var loggedUserId = resourceUtils.getLoggedUserId(securityContext);\n   101→    final var article = createArticle.handle(newArticleRequest.toNewArticleInput(loggedUserId));\n   102→    return Response.ok(resourceUtils.articleResponse(article, loggedUserId))\n   103→        .status(Response.Status.CREATED)\n   104→        .build();\n   105→  }\n   106→\n   107→  @GET\n   108→  @Path(\"/{slug}\")\n   109→  @Produces(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON)\n   110→  public Response findBySlug(\n   111→      @PathParam(\"slug\") @NotBlank(message = ValidationMessages.SLUG_MUST_BE_NOT_BLANK)\n   112→          String slug) {\n   113→    final var article = findArticleBySlug.handle(slug);\n   114→    return Response.ok(resourceUtils.articleResponse(article, null))\n   115→        .status(Response.Status.OK)\n   116→        .build();\n   117→  }\n   118→\n   119→  @PUT\n   120→  @Transactional\n   121→  @Path(\"/{slug}\")\n   122→  @RolesAllowed({\"USER\", \"ADMIN\"})\n   123→  @Consumes(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON)\n   124→  @Produces(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON)\n   125→  public Response update(\n   126→      @PathParam(\"slug\") @NotBlank String slug,\n   127→      @Valid @NotNull UpdateArticleRequest updateArticleRequest,\n   128→      @Context SecurityContext securityContext) {\n   129→    final var loggedUserId = resourceUtils.getLoggedUserId(securityContext);\n   130→    final var updatedArticle =\n   131→        updateArticleBySlug.handle(updateArticleRequest.toUpdateArticleInput(loggedUserId, slug));\n   132→    return Response.ok(resourceUtils.articleResponse(updatedArticle, null))\n   133→        .status(Response.Status.OK)\n   134→        .build();\n   135→  }\n   136→\n   137→  @DELETE\n   138→  @Transactional\n   139→  @Path(\"/{slug}\")\n   140→  @RolesAllowed({\"USER\", \"ADMIN\"})\n   141→  @Produces(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON)\n   142→  public Response delete(\n   143→      @PathParam(\"slug\") @NotBlank(message = ValidationMessages.SLUG_MUST_BE_NOT_BLANK) String slug,\n   144→      @Context SecurityContext securityContext) {\n   145→    final var loggedUserId = resourceUtils.getLoggedUserId(securityContext);\n   146→    deleteArticleBySlug.handle(loggedUserId, slug);\n   147→    return Response.ok().build();\n   148→  }\n   149→\n   150→  @GET\n   151→  @Path(\"/{slug}/comments\")\n   152→  @Produces(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON)\n   153→  public Response getCommentsBySlug(\n   154→      @PathParam(\"slug\") @NotBlank(message = ValidationMessages.SLUG_MUST_BE_NOT_BLANK) String slug,\n   155→      @Context SecurityContext securityContext)\n   156→      throws JsonProcessingException {\n   157→    final var loggedUserId = resourceUtils.getLoggedUserId(securityContext);\n   158→    final var comments = findCommentsByArticleSlug.handle(slug);\n   159→    return Response.ok(\n   160→            objectMapper.writeValueAsString(resourceUtils.commentsResponse(comments, loggedUserId)))\n   161→        .status(Response.Status.OK)\n   162→        .build();\n   163→  }\n   164→\n   165→  @POST\n   166→  @Transactional\n   167→  @Path(\"/{slug}/comments\")\n   168→  @RolesAllowed({\"USER\", \"ADMIN\"})\n   169→  @Consumes(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON)\n   170→  @Produces(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON)\n   171→  public Response createComment(\n   172→      @PathParam(\"slug\") @NotBlank(message = ValidationMessages.SLUG_MUST_BE_NOT_BLANK) String slug,\n   173→      @Valid NewCommentRequest newCommentRequest,\n   174→      @Context SecurityContext securityContext) {\n   175→    final var loggedUserId = resourceUtils.getLoggedUserId(securityContext);\n   176→    final var comment =\n   177→        createComment.handle(newCommentRequest.toNewCommentInput(loggedUserId, slug));\n   178→    return Response.ok(resourceUtils.commentResponse(comment, loggedUserId))\n   179→        .status(Response.Status.OK)\n   180→        .build();\n   181→  }\n   182→\n   183→  @DELETE\n   184→  @Transactional\n   185→  @Path(\"/{slug}/comments/{id}\")\n   186→  @RolesAllowed({\"USER\", \"ADMIN\"})\n   187→  @Produces(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON)\n   188→  public Response deleteComment(\n   189→      @PathParam(\"slug\") @NotBlank(message = ValidationMessages.SLUG_MUST_BE_NOT_BLANK) String slug,\n   190→      @PathParam(\"id\") @NotNull(message = ValidationMessages.COMMENT_ID_MUST_BE_NOT_NULL) UUID id,\n   191→      @Context SecurityContext securityContext) {\n   192→    final var loggedUserId = resourceUtils.getLoggedUserId(securityContext);\n   193→    deleteComment.handle(new DeleteCommentInput(id, loggedUserId, slug));\n   194→    return Response.ok().build();\n   195→  }\n   196→\n   197→  @POST\n   198→  @Transactional\n   199→  @Path(\"/{slug}/favorite\")\n   200→  @RolesAllowed({\"USER\", \"ADMIN\"})\n   201→  @Produces(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON)\n   202→  public Response favoriteArticle(\n   203→      @PathParam(\"slug\") @NotBlank(message = ValidationMessages.SLUG_MUST_BE_NOT_BLANK) String slug,\n   204→      @Context SecurityContext securityContext) {\n   205→    final var loggedUserId = resourceUtils.getLoggedUserId(securityContext);\n   206→    favoriteArticle.handle(slug, loggedUserId);\n   207→    final var article = findArticleBySlug.handle(slug);\n   208→    return Response.ok(resourceUtils.articleResponse(article, loggedUserId))\n   209→        .status(Response.Status.OK)\n   210→        .build();\n   211→  }\n   212→\n   213→  @DELETE\n   214→  @Transactional\n   215→  @Path(\"/{slug}/favorite\")\n   216→  @RolesAllowed({\"USER\", \"ADMIN\"})\n   217→  @Produces(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON)\n   218→  public Response unfavoriteArticle(\n   219→      @PathParam(\"slug\") @NotBlank(message = ValidationMessages.SLUG_MUST_BE_NOT_BLANK) String slug,\n   220→      @Context SecurityContext securityContext) {\n   221→    final var loggedUserId = resourceUtils.getLoggedUserId(securityContext);\n   222→    unfavoriteArticle.handle(slug, loggedUserId);\n   223→    final var article = findArticleBySlug.handle(slug);\n   224→    return Response.ok(resourceUtils.articleResponse(article, loggedUserId))\n   225→        .status(Response.Status.OK)\n   226→        .build();\n   227→  }\n   228→}\n   229→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Miecna5vvBFrf2svJncRik","session_id":"4d21e41c-7b8c-412a-ac18-df8336bdf9ca","uuid":"297237ba-6553-4fc8-90d8-c73140c60b5d"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Miecna5vvBFrf2svJncRik","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Based on my comprehensive search, here are the findings:\n\n@Path Annotated Classes (Full Class Names):\n1. org.example.realworldapi.application.web.resource.ArticlesResource\n2. org.example.realworldapi.application.web.resource.ProfilesResource\n3. org.example.realworldapi.application.web.resource.TagsResource\n4. org.example.realworldapi.application.web.resource.UserResource\n5. org.example.realworldapi.application.web.resource.UsersResource\n6. org.example.realworldapi.RestApplication\n\n@Provider Classes:\n1. org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.web.mapper.BeanValidationExceptionMapper\n2. org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.web.mapper.ExceptionMappers\n3. org.example.realworldapi.RestApplication\n4. org.example.realworldapi.SecurityFilter\n5. org.example.realworldapi.RolesAllowedFilter\n\nAll these classes are part of a Jakarta EE (Quarkus) web application, with the @Path classes primarily being resource classes for different entities like Articles, Profiles, Tags, Users, etc., and the @Provider classes mainly handling exception mapping, security, and application configuration.\n\nWould you like me to provide more details about any of these classes?"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4d21e41c-7b8c-412a-ac18-df8336bdf9ca","uuid":"90147b7b-d653-46dc-9bc2-65585046ed43"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01U95XdvsWo42TUGNZuDr7ks","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\n\nNow I know all the resource and provider classes. The problem is that RESTEasy with an empty `Application` class doesn't automatically scan for `@Path` and `@Provider` classes in a standalone (non-app-server) environment. We need to explicitly register them. Let me fix the `RestApplication` to return the classes:"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":3,"cache_creation_input_tokens":857,"cache_read_input_tokens":35116,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":857,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":508},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4d21e41c-7b8c-412a-ac18-df8336bdf9ca","uuid":"fe7371c5-e5c1-43ba-8743-e579754890db"}
