{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01WudRnXmvcBTMy7dnzfVEEf","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The fix is to add Weld's `org.jboss.weld.environment.servlet.Listener` to the deployment. This listener manages the request scope lifecycle. In the previous attempt, we removed it because it was starting a second CDI container. But the key is: with Weld SE already initialized, the Listener should detect the existing container and just manage the request scope without reinitializing.\n\nAlternatively, we can use Weld's `org.jboss.weld.module.web.servlet.WeldInitialListener` directly which only handles request context management. But the simplest approach is to add the standard listener back. Let me check if there's a better approach - we can also manually activate/deactivate the request context:"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":799,"cache_read_input_tokens":49180,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":799,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":284},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4d21e41c-7b8c-412a-ac18-df8336bdf9ca","uuid":"475b89a3-4721-498f-bce0-d59c1a256a3d"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01WudRnXmvcBTMy7dnzfVEEf","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_bdrk_015E1wETENxjBRJ2XGsNRk9s","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__realworld__quarkus__jakarta/run_1/output/src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/Main.java"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":799,"cache_read_input_tokens":49180,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":799,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":284},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4d21e41c-7b8c-412a-ac18-df8336bdf9ca","uuid":"578e28e4-a74f-42d1-88ac-8abfad6645df"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_015E1wETENxjBRJ2XGsNRk9s","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi;\n     2→\n     3→import io.undertow.Undertow;\n     4→import io.undertow.servlet.Servlets;\n     5→import io.undertow.servlet.api.DeploymentInfo;\n     6→import jakarta.enterprise.inject.spi.BeanManager;\n     7→import org.jboss.resteasy.cdi.CdiInjectorFactory;\n     8→import org.jboss.resteasy.core.ResteasyDeploymentImpl;\n     9→import org.jboss.resteasy.plugins.server.undertow.UndertowJaxrsServer;\n    10→import org.jboss.resteasy.spi.ResteasyDeployment;\n    11→import org.jboss.weld.environment.se.Weld;\n    12→import org.jboss.weld.environment.se.WeldContainer;\n    13→import org.slf4j.Logger;\n    14→import org.slf4j.LoggerFactory;\n    15→\n    16→import java.util.List;\n    17→\n    18→public class Main {\n    19→\n    20→    private static final Logger LOG = LoggerFactory.getLogger(Main.class);\n    21→\n    22→    public static void main(String[] args) throws Exception {\n    23→        int port = Integer.parseInt(System.getenv().getOrDefault(\"PORT\", \"8080\"));\n    24→        String host = System.getenv().getOrDefault(\"HOST\", \"0.0.0.0\");\n    25→\n    26→        // Initialize Weld CDI container\n    27→        Weld weld = new Weld();\n    28→        WeldContainer container = weld.initialize();\n    29→        LOG.info(\"CDI container initialized\");\n    30→\n    31→        // Initialize JPA\n    32→        EntityManagerProducer emProducer = container.select(EntityManagerProducer.class).get();\n    33→        LOG.info(\"JPA EntityManager ready\");\n    34→\n    35→        // Configure RESTEasy with CDI\n    36→        ResteasyDeployment deployment = new ResteasyDeploymentImpl();\n    37→        deployment.setInjectorFactoryClass(CdiInjectorFactory.class.getName());\n    38→\n    39→        // Register JAX-RS resource classes\n    40→        deployment.setScannedResourceClasses(List.of(\n    41→            \"org.example.realworldapi.application.web.resource.ArticlesResource\",\n    42→            \"org.example.realworldapi.application.web.resource.ProfilesResource\",\n    43→            \"org.example.realworldapi.application.web.resource.TagsResource\",\n    44→            \"org.example.realworldapi.application.web.resource.UserResource\",\n    45→            \"org.example.realworldapi.application.web.resource.UsersResource\"\n    46→        ));\n    47→\n    48→        // Register JAX-RS provider classes\n    49→        deployment.setScannedProviderClasses(List.of(\n    50→            \"org.example.realworldapi.SecurityFilter\",\n    51→            \"org.example.realworldapi.RolesAllowedFilter\",\n    52→            \"org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.web.mapper.BeanValidationExceptionMapper\",\n    53→            \"org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.web.mapper.ExceptionMappers\"\n    54→        ));\n    55→\n    56→        // Build Undertow deployment\n    57→        BeanManager beanManager = container.getBeanManager();\n    58→        DeploymentInfo di = new DeploymentInfo()\n    59→                .addServletContextAttribute(ResteasyDeployment.class.getName(), deployment)\n    60→                .addServletContextAttribute(\"jakarta.enterprise.inject.spi.BeanManager\", beanManager)\n    61→                .setContextPath(\"/api\")\n    62→                .setDeploymentName(\"ResteasyUndertow\")\n    63→                .setClassLoader(Main.class.getClassLoader())\n    64→                .addServlet(\n    65→                    Servlets.servlet(\"ResteasyServlet\",\n    66→                        org.jboss.resteasy.plugins.server.servlet.HttpServletDispatcher.class)\n    67→                        .setAsyncSupported(true)\n    68→                        .setLoadOnStartup(1)\n    69→                        .addMapping(\"/*\")\n    70→                );\n    71→\n    72→        UndertowJaxrsServer server = new UndertowJaxrsServer();\n    73→        server.start(\n    74→            Undertow.builder()\n    75→                .addHttpListener(port, host)\n    76→        );\n    77→        server.deploy(di);\n    78→\n    79→        LOG.info(\"RealWorld API started on port {}\", port);\n    80→        LOG.info(\"API available at http://{}:{}/api\", host, port);\n    81→\n    82→        Runtime.getRuntime().addShutdownHook(new Thread(() -> {\n    83→            LOG.info(\"Shutting down...\");\n    84→            server.stop();\n    85→            container.close();\n    86→        }));\n    87→    }\n    88→}\n    89→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4d21e41c-7b8c-412a-ac18-df8336bdf9ca","uuid":"f8100d3f-1d52-4b10-8b6a-e5b9f275a9da"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01W2YXEmrcp4zqcbQknNGVyv","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I need to add the Weld listener to manage request scoping. The `org.jboss.weld.environment.servlet.Listener` both starts Weld and manages request context. Since we already started Weld SE, we need to prevent it from initializing another container. The trick is to set the `org.jboss.weld.environment.container.class` servlet context attribute to tell it Weld is already there.\n\nActually, a cleaner approach: add a `ListenerInfo` for `org.jboss.weld.environment.servlet.Listener` to the deployment. When the listener sees that `CDI.current()` already returns a container, it should just handle request context management without reinitializing."}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1825,"cache_read_input_tokens":49979,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1825,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":1438},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4d21e41c-7b8c-412a-ac18-df8336bdf9ca","uuid":"aceedf41-37ed-464c-b339-2429928a4a2b"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01W2YXEmrcp4zqcbQknNGVyv","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_bdrk_01A19MiK9jxKGx3xAGm2b6YS","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__realworld__quarkus__jakarta/run_1/output/src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/Main.java","content":"package org.example.realworldapi;\n\nimport io.undertow.Undertow;\nimport io.undertow.servlet.Servlets;\nimport io.undertow.servlet.api.DeploymentInfo;\nimport io.undertow.servlet.api.ListenerInfo;\nimport jakarta.enterprise.inject.spi.BeanManager;\nimport org.jboss.resteasy.cdi.CdiInjectorFactory;\nimport org.jboss.resteasy.core.ResteasyDeploymentImpl;\nimport org.jboss.resteasy.plugins.server.undertow.UndertowJaxrsServer;\nimport org.jboss.resteasy.spi.ResteasyDeployment;\nimport org.jboss.weld.environment.se.Weld;\nimport org.jboss.weld.environment.se.WeldContainer;\nimport org.jboss.weld.environment.servlet.Listener;\nimport org.slf4j.Logger;\nimport org.slf4j.LoggerFactory;\n\nimport java.util.List;\n\npublic class Main {\n\n    private static final Logger LOG = LoggerFactory.getLogger(Main.class);\n\n    public static void main(String[] args) throws Exception {\n        int port = Integer.parseInt(System.getenv().getOrDefault(\"PORT\", \"8080\"));\n        String host = System.getenv().getOrDefault(\"HOST\", \"0.0.0.0\");\n\n        // Initialize Weld CDI container\n        Weld weld = new Weld();\n        WeldContainer container = weld.initialize();\n        LOG.info(\"CDI container initialized\");\n\n        // Initialize JPA\n        EntityManagerProducer emProducer = container.select(EntityManagerProducer.class).get();\n        LOG.info(\"JPA EntityManager ready\");\n\n        // Configure RESTEasy with CDI\n        ResteasyDeployment deployment = new ResteasyDeploymentImpl();\n        deployment.setInjectorFactoryClass(CdiInjectorFactory.class.getName());\n\n        // Register JAX-RS resource classes\n        deployment.setScannedResourceClasses(List.of(\n            \"org.example.realworldapi.application.web.resource.ArticlesResource\",\n            \"org.example.realworldapi.application.web.resource.ProfilesResource\",\n            \"org.example.realworldapi.application.web.resource.TagsResource\",\n            \"org.example.realworldapi.application.web.resource.UserResource\",\n            \"org.example.realworldapi.application.web.resource.UsersResource\"\n        ));\n\n        // Register JAX-RS provider classes\n        deployment.setScannedProviderClasses(List.of(\n            \"org.example.realworldapi.SecurityFilter\",\n            \"org.example.realworldapi.RolesAllowedFilter\",\n            \"org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.web.mapper.BeanValidationExceptionMapper\",\n            \"org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.web.mapper.ExceptionMappers\"\n        ));\n\n        // Build Undertow deployment\n        BeanManager beanManager = container.getBeanManager();\n        DeploymentInfo di = new DeploymentInfo()\n                .addServletContextAttribute(ResteasyDeployment.class.getName(), deployment)\n                .addServletContextAttribute(\"jakarta.enterprise.inject.spi.BeanManager\", beanManager)\n                .setContextPath(\"/api\")\n                .setDeploymentName(\"ResteasyUndertow\")\n                .setClassLoader(Main.class.getClassLoader())\n                // Add Weld listener to manage request/session scopes for each HTTP request\n                .addListener(new ListenerInfo(Listener.class))\n                .addServlet(\n                    Servlets.servlet(\"ResteasyServlet\",\n                        org.jboss.resteasy.plugins.server.servlet.HttpServletDispatcher.class)\n                        .setAsyncSupported(true)\n                        .setLoadOnStartup(1)\n                        .addMapping(\"/*\")\n                );\n\n        UndertowJaxrsServer server = new UndertowJaxrsServer();\n        server.start(\n            Undertow.builder()\n                .addHttpListener(port, host)\n        );\n        server.deploy(di);\n\n        LOG.info(\"RealWorld API started on port {}\", port);\n        LOG.info(\"API available at http://{}:{}/api\", host, port);\n\n        Runtime.getRuntime().addShutdownHook(new Thread(() -> {\n            LOG.info(\"Shutting down...\");\n            server.stop();\n            container.close();\n        }));\n    }\n}\n"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1825,"cache_read_input_tokens":49979,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1825,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":1438},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4d21e41c-7b8c-412a-ac18-df8336bdf9ca","uuid":"ae744538-bfd4-49a5-bd59-a5a564cb1313"}
