{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01PuDqdcy3GYzeNbMJKWtWGC","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.application.web.model.request;\n     2→\n     3→import com.fasterxml.jackson.annotation.JsonRootName;\n     4→import jakarta.validation.constraints.NotBlank;\n     5→import lombok.Getter;\n     6→import lombok.Setter;\n     7→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.constants.ValidationMessages;\n     8→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.user.CreateUserInput;\n     9→\n    10→@Getter\n    11→@Setter\n    12→@JsonRootName(\"user\")\n    13→public class NewUserRequest {\n    14→  @NotBlank(message = ValidationMessages.USERNAME_MUST_BE_NOT_BLANK)\n    15→  private String username;\n    16→\n    17→  @NotBlank(message = ValidationMessages.EMAIL_MUST_BE_NOT_BLANK)\n    18→  private String email;\n    19→\n    20→  @NotBlank(message = ValidationMessages.PASSWORD_MUST_BE_NOT_BLANK)\n    21→  private String password;\n    22→\n    23→  public CreateUserInput toCreateUserInput() {\n    24→    return new CreateUserInput(this.username, this.email, this.password);\n    25→  }\n    26→}\n    27→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_012GnKNgrfTU73YiptDJdpse","session_id":"4d21e41c-7b8c-412a-ac18-df8336bdf9ca","uuid":"5d62e54f-a5b2-40aa-b9a9-917254a6629b"}
