{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_018Rs1ZdEc5kfW18zKh2TwhC","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.application.web.model.response;\n     2→\n     3→import com.fasterxml.jackson.annotation.JsonRootName;\n     4→import lombok.Getter;\n     5→import lombok.NoArgsConstructor;\n     6→import lombok.Setter;\n     7→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.user.User;\n     8→\n     9→@Getter\n    10→@Setter\n    11→@NoArgsConstructor\n    12→@JsonRootName(\"user\")\n    13→public class UserResponse {\n    14→\n    15→  private String username;\n    16→  private String bio;\n    17→  private String image;\n    18→  private String email;\n    19→  private String token;\n    20→\n    21→  public UserResponse(User user, String token) {\n    22→    this.username = user.getUsername();\n    23→    this.bio = user.getBio();\n    24→    this.image = user.getImage();\n    25→    this.email = user.getEmail();\n    26→    this.token = token;\n    27→  }\n    28→}\n    29→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_012GnKNgrfTU73YiptDJdpse","session_id":"4d21e41c-7b8c-412a-ac18-df8336bdf9ca","uuid":"28acca0a-4dc4-487f-9c74-1300a58690ce"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_012GnKNgrfTU73YiptDJdpse","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I've retrieved the complete contents of the three files you requested:\n\n1. UsersResource.java: A JAX-RS resource for user registration and login, with two main methods:\n   - `create()`: Handles user registration, creates a new user, generates a JWT token\n   - `login()`: Handles user login, validates credentials, generates a JWT token\n\n2. NewUserRequest.java: A DTO (Data Transfer Object) for new user registration, containing:\n   - Username\n   - Email\n   - Password\n   - A method `toCreateUserInput()` to convert the request to a domain input object\n\n3. UserResponse.java: A DTO for user response after registration or login, containing:\n   - Username\n   - Bio\n   - Image\n   - Email\n   - Token\n   - A constructor that maps a User domain object and token to the response\n\nWould you like me to elaborate on any of these files or explain their interactions?"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4d21e41c-7b8c-412a-ac18-df8336bdf9ca","uuid":"6a91c9f2-bddb-48c5-8055-e8a68f2edfef"}
