{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_017qiLi318yuWaf1cCYgtnqi","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.application.web.model.request;\n     2→\n     3→import com.fasterxml.jackson.annotation.JsonRootName;\n     4→import jakarta.validation.constraints.NotBlank;\n     5→import lombok.Getter;\n     6→import lombok.Setter;\n     7→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.constants.ValidationMessages;\n     8→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.user.CreateUserInput;\n     9→\n    10→@Getter\n    11→@Setter\n    12→@JsonRootName(\"user\")\n    13→public class NewUserRequest {\n    14→  @NotBlank(message = ValidationMessages.USERNAME_MUST_BE_NOT_BLANK)\n    15→  private String username;\n    16→\n    17→  @NotBlank(message = ValidationMessages.EMAIL_MUST_BE_NOT_BLANK)\n    18→  private String email;\n    19→\n    20→  @NotBlank(message = ValidationMessages.PASSWORD_MUST_BE_NOT_BLANK)\n    21→  private String password;\n    22→\n    23→  public CreateUserInput toCreateUserInput() {\n    24→    return new CreateUserInput(this.username, this.email, this.password);\n    25→  }\n    26→}\n    27→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4d21e41c-7b8c-412a-ac18-df8336bdf9ca","uuid":"9545f8e6-93d3-4ba8-a65d-78e3279574f8"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01SgB9tVZ3utdXBxK2fLfr7a","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.application.web.resource;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.enterprise.context.RequestScoped;\n     4→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n     5→import jakarta.transaction.Transactional;\n     6→import jakarta.validation.Valid;\n     7→import jakarta.validation.constraints.NotNull;\n     8→import jakarta.ws.rs.Consumes;\n     9→import jakarta.ws.rs.NotAuthorizedException;\n    10→import jakarta.ws.rs.POST;\n    11→import jakarta.ws.rs.Path;\n    12→import jakarta.ws.rs.Produces;\n    13→import jakarta.ws.rs.core.MediaType;\n    14→import jakarta.ws.rs.core.Response;\n    15→import org.example.realworldapi.application.web.model.request.LoginRequest;\n    16→import org.example.realworldapi.application.web.model.request.NewUserRequest;\n    17→import org.example.realworldapi.application.web.model.response.UserResponse;\n    18→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.exception.InvalidPasswordException;\n    19→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.exception.UserNotFoundException;\n    20→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.CreateUser;\n    21→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.LoginUser;\n    22→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.constants.ValidationMessages;\n    23→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.user.User;\n    24→import org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.provider.JwtTokenProvider;\n    25→\n    26→@RequestScoped\n    27→@Path(\"/users\")\n    28→public class UsersResource {\n    29→\n    30→  @Inject private CreateUser createUser;\n    31→  @Inject private LoginUser loginUser;\n    32→  @Inject private JwtTokenProvider tokenProvider;\n    33→\n    34→  @POST\n    35→  @Transactional\n    36→  @Consumes(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON)\n    37→  @Produces(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON)\n    38→  public Response create(\n    39→      @Valid @NotNull(message = ValidationMessages.REQUEST_BODY_MUST_BE_NOT_NULL)\n    40→          NewUserRequest newUserRequest) {\n    41→    final var user = createUser.handle(newUserRequest.toCreateUserInput());\n    42→    final var token = tokenProvider.createUserToken(user.getId().toString());\n    43→    return Response.ok(new UserResponse(user, token)).status(Response.Status.CREATED).build();\n    44→  }\n    45→\n    46→  @POST\n    47→  @Path(\"/login\")\n    48→  @Consumes(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON)\n    49→  @Produces(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON)\n    50→  public Response login(\n    51→      @Valid @NotNull(message = ValidationMessages.REQUEST_BODY_MUST_BE_NOT_NULL)\n    52→          LoginRequest loginRequest) {\n    53→    User user;\n    54→    try {\n    55→      user = loginUser.handle(loginRequest.toLoginUserInput());\n    56→    } catch (UserNotFoundException | InvalidPasswordException ex) {\n    57→      throw new NotAuthorizedException(\"Unauthorized\");\n    58→    }\n    59→    final var token = tokenProvider.createUserToken(user.getId().toString());\n    60→    return Response.ok(new UserResponse(user, token)).status(Response.Status.OK).build();\n    61→  }\n    62→}\n    63→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4d21e41c-7b8c-412a-ac18-df8336bdf9ca","uuid":"e98eeafa-635d-4cd9-b80b-242b3335e31d"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_015aj4Vkr8MVfLPFBWbr78WR","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I see - `NewUserRequest` has `@JsonRootName(\"user\")` and the ObjectMapper has `UNWRAP_ROOT_VALUE` enabled. So the request body `{\"user\":{...}}` should work. But the error is `Not able to deserialize data provided` which is a RESTEasy-Jackson error.\n\nThe issue might be that RESTEasy is using its own ObjectMapper, not our CDI-produced one. The `resteasy-jackson2-provider` creates its own ObjectMapper by default. We need to configure RESTEasy to use our CDI ObjectMapper that has `UNWRAP_ROOT_VALUE`/`WRAP_ROOT_VALUE` enabled.\n\nLet me check if there's a custom Jackson provider or context resolver:"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1920,"cache_read_input_tokens":59763,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1920,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":434},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4d21e41c-7b8c-412a-ac18-df8336bdf9ca","uuid":"2a6a7739-7ac5-49dd-b8f1-29e0a9532864"}
