{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01D9d6QZHoKxQS1gF54JamK3","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Still getting the `WELD-001303: No active contexts for scope type jakarta.enterprise.context.RequestScoped` error. The Weld Listener isn't activating the request context properly. This is likely because the listener is initializing a *second* Weld container in the servlet context, and the request scope is only active in the first (SE) container's context.\n\nI see the problem now: when we use Weld SE + servlet listener, there's a mismatch. The Weld SE CDI container beans are registered in one context, but the Weld servlet listener manages request contexts for a different (servlet) context. \n\nThe better approach is to use `org.jboss.weld.environment.servlet.EnhancedListener` or to avoid using @RequestScoped altogether on the resource classes and instead just use `@Dependent`. Let me try changing the resource scope to `@Dependent` since that doesn't require request context:"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":965,"cache_read_input_tokens":73406,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":965,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":468},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4d21e41c-7b8c-412a-ac18-df8336bdf9ca","uuid":"f230ad4a-4afc-4f53-bf32-b9919377c217"}
