{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01SdLY2saAxQh5tzVHPELHXY","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.annotation.PostConstruct;\n     4→import jakarta.annotation.PreDestroy;\n     5→import jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\n     6→import jakarta.enterprise.context.RequestScoped;\n     7→import jakarta.enterprise.inject.Disposes;\n     8→import jakarta.enterprise.inject.Produces;\n     9→import jakarta.persistence.EntityManager;\n    10→import jakarta.persistence.EntityManagerFactory;\n    11→import jakarta.persistence.Persistence;\n    12→import org.slf4j.Logger;\n    13→import org.slf4j.LoggerFactory;\n    14→\n    15→import java.util.HashMap;\n    16→import java.util.Map;\n    17→\n    18→@ApplicationScoped\n    19→public class EntityManagerProducer {\n    20→\n    21→    private static final Logger LOG = LoggerFactory.getLogger(EntityManagerProducer.class);\n    22→    private EntityManagerFactory emf;\n    23→\n    24→    @PostConstruct\n    25→    public void init() {\n    26→        Map<String, String> props = new HashMap<>();\n    27→\n    28→        // Allow environment variables to override persistence.xml settings\n    29→        String jdbcUrl = System.getenv(\"JDBC_URL\");\n    30→        String dbUser = System.getenv(\"DB_USERNAME\");\n    31→        String dbPass = System.getenv(\"DB_PASSWORD\");\n    32→\n    33→        if (jdbcUrl != null) {\n    34→            props.put(\"jakarta.persistence.jdbc.url\", jdbcUrl);\n    35→        }\n    36→        if (dbUser != null) {\n    37→            props.put(\"jakarta.persistence.jdbc.user\", dbUser);\n    38→        }\n    39→        if (dbPass != null) {\n    40→            props.put(\"jakarta.persistence.jdbc.password\", dbPass);\n    41→        }\n    42→\n    43→        emf = Persistence.createEntityManagerFactory(\"realworld\", props);\n    44→        LOG.info(\"EntityManagerFactory created\");\n    45→    }\n    46→\n    47→    @Produces\n    48→    @RequestScoped\n    49→    public EntityManager createEntityManager() {\n    50→        return emf.createEntityManager();\n    51→    }\n    52→\n    53→    public void closeEntityManager(@Disposes EntityManager em) {\n    54→        if (em.isOpen()) {\n    55→            em.close();\n    56→        }\n    57→    }\n    58→\n    59→    @PreDestroy\n    60→    public void close() {\n    61→        if (emf != null && emf.isOpen()) {\n    62→            emf.close();\n    63→        }\n    64→    }\n    65→\n    66→    public EntityManagerFactory getEntityManagerFactory() {\n    67→        return emf;\n    68→    }\n    69→}\n    70→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4d21e41c-7b8c-412a-ac18-df8336bdf9ca","uuid":"95e10540-7aea-4794-ae42-e752e3579ebc"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_011L98aEa9ogiYvaaUnpubfY","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The `@RequestScoped` EntityManager producer is the root cause. Since Weld SE doesn't have a request context, we can't use `@RequestScoped`. But we don't want to make EntityManager `@ApplicationScoped` either since EntityManagers are not thread-safe.\n\nThe real fix here is to change the EntityManager to `@Dependent` scope. In `@Dependent` scope, each injection point gets its own instance, and it's disposed when the enclosing bean is disposed. Since the resources are now `@Dependent` too, the EntityManager will be created per resource instance, which is what we want."}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1456,"cache_read_input_tokens":76429,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1456,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":316},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4d21e41c-7b8c-412a-ac18-df8336bdf9ca","uuid":"12bc8387-a5cd-4b06-bf43-1921cf4a8848"}
