{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01S1TNghEDgWbzCc937E9WDt","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.application.web.model.request;\n     2→\n     3→import com.fasterxml.jackson.annotation.JsonRootName;\n     4→import jakarta.validation.constraints.NotBlank;\n     5→import lombok.Getter;\n     6→import lombok.Setter;\n     7→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.constants.ValidationMessages;\n     8→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.user.LoginUserInput;\n     9→\n    10→@Getter\n    11→@Setter\n    12→@JsonRootName(\"user\")\n    13→public class LoginRequest {\n    14→\n    15→  @NotBlank(message = ValidationMessages.EMAIL_MUST_BE_NOT_BLANK)\n    16→  private String email;\n    17→\n    18→  @NotBlank(message = ValidationMessages.PASSWORD_MUST_BE_NOT_BLANK)\n    19→  private String password;\n    20→\n    21→  public LoginUserInput toLoginUserInput() {\n    22→    return new LoginUserInput(this.email, this.password);\n    23→  }\n    24→}\n    25→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01CoasTLqMjoZUamJHataGM4","session_id":"4d21e41c-7b8c-412a-ac18-df8336bdf9ca","uuid":"25d18965-b3cf-4583-a45f-a8c1ba53fb5b"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Na7khqst1KJyEG6TWaHq8o","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.application.web.resource;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.enterprise.context.Dependent;\n     4→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n     5→import jakarta.transaction.Transactional;\n     6→import jakarta.validation.Valid;\n     7→import jakarta.validation.constraints.NotNull;\n     8→import jakarta.ws.rs.Consumes;\n     9→import jakarta.ws.rs.NotAuthorizedException;\n    10→import jakarta.ws.rs.POST;\n    11→import jakarta.ws.rs.Path;\n    12→import jakarta.ws.rs.Produces;\n    13→import jakarta.ws.rs.core.MediaType;\n    14→import jakarta.ws.rs.core.Response;\n    15→import org.example.realworldapi.application.web.model.request.LoginRequest;\n    16→import org.example.realworldapi.application.web.model.request.NewUserRequest;\n    17→import org.example.realworldapi.application.web.model.response.UserResponse;\n    18→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.exception.InvalidPasswordException;\n    19→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.exception.UserNotFoundException;\n    20→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.CreateUser;\n    21→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.LoginUser;\n    22→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.constants.ValidationMessages;\n    23→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.user.User;\n    24→import org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.provider.JwtTokenProvider;\n    25→\n    26→@Dependent\n    27→@Path(\"/users\")\n    28→public class UsersResource {\n    29→\n    30→  @Inject private CreateUser createUser;\n    31→  @Inject private LoginUser loginUser;\n    32→  @Inject private JwtTokenProvider tokenProvider;\n    33→\n    34→  @POST\n    35→  @Transactional\n    36→  @Consumes(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON)\n    37→  @Produces(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON)\n    38→  public Response create(\n    39→      @Valid @NotNull(message = ValidationMessages.REQUEST_BODY_MUST_BE_NOT_NULL)\n    40→          NewUserRequest newUserRequest) {\n    41→    final var user = createUser.handle(newUserRequest.toCreateUserInput());\n    42→    final var token = tokenProvider.createUserToken(user.getId().toString());\n    43→    return Response.ok(new UserResponse(user, token)).status(Response.Status.CREATED).build();\n    44→  }\n    45→\n    46→  @POST\n    47→  @Path(\"/login\")\n    48→  @Consumes(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON)\n    49→  @Produces(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON)\n    50→  public Response login(\n    51→      @Valid @NotNull(message = ValidationMessages.REQUEST_BODY_MUST_BE_NOT_NULL)\n    52→          LoginRequest loginRequest) {\n    53→    User user;\n    54→    try {\n    55→      user = loginUser.handle(loginRequest.toLoginUserInput());\n    56→    } catch (UserNotFoundException | InvalidPasswordException ex) {\n    57→      throw new NotAuthorizedException(\"Unauthorized\");\n    58→    }\n    59→    final var token = tokenProvider.createUserToken(user.getId().toString());\n    60→    return Response.ok(new UserResponse(user, token)).status(Response.Status.OK).build();\n    61→  }\n    62→}\n    63→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01CoasTLqMjoZUamJHataGM4","session_id":"4d21e41c-7b8c-412a-ac18-df8336bdf9ca","uuid":"2fd4bae5-96e5-409e-9069-23b9a8f1b24f"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01D44F5dtKU7jDqgBN15oAdi","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature;\n     2→\n     3→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.user.LoginUserInput;\n     4→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.user.User;\n     5→\n     6→public interface LoginUser {\n     7→  User handle(LoginUserInput loginUserInput);\n     8→}\n     9→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01CoasTLqMjoZUamJHataGM4","session_id":"4d21e41c-7b8c-412a-ac18-df8336bdf9ca","uuid":"d6ce4971-fbb9-438d-9b77-fb23d131ea7b"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01EKGw83A98EG6oztnPe4v84","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.impl;\n     2→\n     3→import lombok.AllArgsConstructor;\n     4→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.exception.InvalidPasswordException;\n     5→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.exception.UserNotFoundException;\n     6→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.LoginUser;\n     7→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.provider.HashProvider;\n     8→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.user.LoginUserInput;\n     9→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.user.User;\n    10→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.user.UserRepository;\n    11→\n    12→@AllArgsConstructor\n    13→public class LoginUserImpl implements LoginUser {\n    14→\n    15→  private final UserRepository userRepository;\n    16→  private final HashProvider hashProvider;\n    17→\n    18→  @Override\n    19→  public User handle(LoginUserInput loginUserInput) {\n    20→    final var user =\n    21→        userRepository\n    22→            .findByEmail(loginUserInput.getEmail())\n    23→            .orElseThrow(UserNotFoundException::new);\n    24→    if (!isPasswordValid(loginUserInput.getPassword(), user.getPassword())) {\n    25→      throw new InvalidPasswordException();\n    26→    }\n    27→    return user;\n    28→  }\n    29→\n    30→  private boolean isPasswordValid(String password, String hashedPassword) {\n    31→    return hashProvider.checkPassword(password, hashedPassword);\n    32→  }\n    33→}\n    34→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_