{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01JHo132cuAyEgHF74WrC3aV","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! I have successfully added the `@Transactional` annotation to all the necessary endpoint methods across all 5 JAX-RS resource files. Let me provide you with a summary of the changes:\n\n## Summary of Changes\n\nAll 5 JAX-RS resource files have been updated with `@Transactional` annotations on endpoint methods that access the database.\n\n### 1. **ArticlesResource.java**\n   - `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__realworld__quarkus__jakarta/run_1/output/src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/application/web/resource/ArticlesResource.java`\n   - Added `@Transactional` to 4 methods:\n     - `feed()` - GET /articles/feed\n     - `getArticles()` - GET /articles\n     - `findBySlug()` - GET /articles/{slug}\n     - `getCommentsBySlug()` - GET /articles/{slug}/comments\n   - Note: Methods `create()`, `update()`, `delete()`, `createComment()`, `deleteComment()`, `favoriteArticle()`, and `unfavoriteArticle()` already had `@Transactional`\n   - Import was already present: `import jakarta.transaction.Transactional;`\n\n### 2. **ProfilesResource.java**\n   - `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__realworld__quarkus__jakarta/run_1/output/src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/application/web/resource/ProfilesResource.java`\n   - Added `@Transactional` to 1 method:\n     - `getProfile()` - GET /profiles/{username}\n   - Note: Methods `follow()` and `unfollow()` already had `@Transactional`\n   - Import was already present: `import jakarta.transaction.Transactional;`\n\n### 3. **TagsResource.java**\n   - `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__realworld__quarkus__jakarta/run_1/output/src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/application/web/resource/TagsResource.java`\n   - Added `@Transactional` to 1 method:\n     - `getTags()` - GET /tags\n   - Added the import: `import jakarta.transaction.Transactional;`\n\n### 4. **UserResource.java**\n   - `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__realworld__quarkus__jakarta/run_1/output/src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/application/web/resource/UserResource.java`\n   - Added `@Transactional` to 1 method:\n     - `getUser()` - GET /user\n   - Note: Method `update()` already had `@Transactional`\n   - Import was already present: `import jakarta.transaction.Transactional;`\n\n### 5. **UsersResource.java**\n   - `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__realworld__quarkus__jakarta/run_1/output/src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/application/web/resource/UsersResource.java`\n   - Added `@Transactional` to 1 method:\n     - `login()` - POST /users/login\n   - Note: Method `create()` already had `@Transactional`\n   - Import was already present: `import jakarta.transaction.Transactional;`\n\n## Total Changes\n- **8 methods** now have `@Transactional` annotation added\n- **1 file** (TagsResource.java) had the import statement added\n- All other files already had the necessary import statement\n\nAll public endpoint methods (annotated with @GET, @POST, @PUT, @DELETE) that access the database now have the `@Transactional` annotation, ensuring proper transaction management for database operations."}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4d21e41c-7b8c-412a-ac18-df8336bdf9ca","uuid":"db6d399f-73f1-407d-a0fc-59b33cef2025"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_014gSLZZtWkc6SUf79h6Lfm5","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\n\nGood. Now there's a subtle issue: with the `@Dependent` scope and the thread-local EntityManager, the interceptor and the repositories will share the same EntityManager instance for the same thread. But there's still a problem - the `@Dependent` injection happens at bean creation time. For `@ApplicationScoped` repository beans, the EntityManager is injected once when the bean proxy is first used. Subsequent calls will use that same (now-closed) EntityManager.\n\nWait - actually with `@Dependent` produced beans, CDI creates a new instance for each injection point. For `@ApplicationScoped` beans like the repositories, the EM is injected once. But our producer now returns the thread-local EM, so even though the field was injected once, it could be a stale reference.\n\nThe real solution: the repositories' `em` field should call the producer each time, not hold a stale reference. Since `@Dependent` beans aren't proxied, the injected EM is a direct reference. I need a different approach.\n\nLet me change the approach: make the EntityManager `@ApplicationScoped` with a proxy that delegates to the thread-local on each call. Actually, the simplest approach that works: use a CDI `Instance<EntityManager>` in the abstract repository or use a provider pattern.\n\nActually, the simplest fix: change `AbstractPanacheRepository` to not use field injection for EntityManager. Instead, have it call a static method on `EntityManagerProducer` to get the current thread-local EM:"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":3,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1942,"cache_read_input_tokens":115940,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1942,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":476},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4d21e41c-7b8c-412a-ac18-df8336bdf9ca","uuid":"077c8e42-aefe-45e7-86d7-4ca0d543c84f"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_014gSLZZtWkc6SUf79h6Lfm5","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_bdrk_01KDyVnHXxaBxv9CGvDqL1aG","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__realworld__quarkus__jakarta/run_1/output/src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/infrastructure/repository/hibernate/panache/AbstractPanacheRepository.java"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":3,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1942,"cache_read_input_tokens":115940,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1942,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":476},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4d21e41c-7b8c-412a-ac18-df8336bdf9ca","uuid":"25f33b61-685b-403c-bd35-6d10ab9c8095"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01KDyVnHXxaBxv9CGvDqL1aG","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.repository.hibernate.panache;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n     4→import jakarta.persistence.EntityManager;\n     5→import java.util.List;\n     6→import java.util.UUID;\n     7→import java.util.stream.Collectors;\n     8→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article.FavoriteRelationship;\n     9→import org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.repository.hibernate.entity.*;\n    10→\n    11→public abstract class AbstractPanacheRepository {\n    12→\n    13→  @Inject protected EntityManager em;\n    14→\n    15→  protected UserEntity findUserEntityById(UUID id) {\n    16→    return em.find(UserEntity.class, id);\n    17→  }\n    18→\n    19→  protected TagEntity findTagEntityById(UUID id) {\n    20→    return em.find(TagEntity.class, id);\n    21→  }\n    22→\n    23→  protected ArticleEntity findArticleEntityById(UUID id) {\n    24→    return em.find(ArticleEntity.class, id);\n    25→  }\n    26→\n    27→  protected CommentEntity findCommentEntityById(UUID id) {\n    28→    return em.find(CommentEntity.class, id);\n    29→  }\n    30→\n    31→  protected FavoriteRelationshipEntity findFavoriteRelationshipEntityByKey(\n    32→      FavoriteRelationship favoriteRelationship) {\n    33→\n    34→    final var userEntity = findUserEntityById(favoriteRelationship.getUser().getId());\n    35→    final var articleEntity = findArticleEntityById(favoriteRelationship.getArticle().getId());\n    36→\n    37→    final var favoriteRelationshipEntityKey = new FavoriteRelationshipEntityKey();\n    38→    favoriteRelationshipEntityKey.setUser(userEntity);\n    39→    favoriteRelationshipEntityKey.setArticle(articleEntity);\n    40→\n    41→    return em.find(FavoriteRelationshipEntity.class, favoriteRelationshipEntityKey);\n    42→  }\n    43→\n    44→  protected boolean isNotEmpty(List<?> list) {\n    45→    return list != null && !list.isEmpty();\n    46→  }\n    47→\n    48→  protected List<String> toUpperCase(List<String> subjectList) {\n    49→    return subjectList.stream().map(String::toUpperCase).collect(Collectors.toList());\n    50→  }\n    51→}\n    52→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4d21e41c-7b8c-412a-ac18-df8336bdf9ca","uuid":"7754b4cd-4750-4759-b69d-9f0c33ac1488"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01LVroZmUgV6kMi5N3H98ZoQ","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I see the problem. The `@Inject protected EntityManager em` in `AbstractPanacheRepository` will get injected once (when the `@ApplicationScoped` repository bean is created). After the first request, the `TransactionalInterceptor` closes the EM via `closeCurrentEntityManager()`. Subsequent requests will have a closed EM in the repository.\n\nThe best approach: add a static `getCurrentEntityManager()` method to `EntityManagerProducer` and have the abstract repository call it dynamically instead of using field injection. Let me update both files:"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1435,"cache_read_input_tokens":117882,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1435,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":490},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4d21e41c-7b8c-412a-ac18-df8336bdf9ca","uuid":"9435f1e6-6e9a-479c-a9a0-67e73ce9d09b"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01LVroZmUgV6kMi5N3H98ZoQ","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_bdrk_01F3gmH9bUfag8e8QqtAkvjK","name":"Edit","input":{"file_path":"/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__realworld__quarkus__jakarta/run_1/output/src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/EntityManagerProducer.java","old_string":"    /**\n     * Close and remove the thread-local EntityManager.\n     * Called by the TransactionalInterceptor after transaction completes.\n     */\n    public static void closeCurrentEntityManager() {","new_string":"    /**\n     * Get the current thread-local EntityManager (creating one if needed).\n     * Used by repositories to always get the current request's EM.\n     */\n    public static EntityManager getCurrentEntityManager() {\n        EntityManager em = threadLocalEm.get();\n        if (em == null || !em.isOpen()) {\n            throw new IllegalStateException(\"No active EntityManager for current thread. Ensure @Transactional is present.\");\n        }\n        return em;\n    }\n\n    /**\n     * Close and remove the thread-local EntityManager.\n     * Called by the TransactionalInterceptor after transaction completes.\n     */\n    public static void closeCurrentEntityManager() {"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1435,"cache_read_input_tokens":117882,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1435,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":490},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4d21e41c-7b8c-412a-ac18-df8336bdf9ca","uuid":"ac040963-75f5-46ab-9694-7eb6a3a2410e"}
