{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01FV1uJHXHvMWmx4fLiXSrH4","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_bdrk_01PvTmr5gUZX2xBWznHGjRJ5","name":"Task","input":{"description":"Replace em with getEm() in repos","prompt":"In the directory /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__realworld__quarkus__jakarta/run_1/output/src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/infrastructure/repository/hibernate/panache/, there are 7 repository files that extend AbstractPanacheRepository:\n\n1. ArticleRepositoryPanache.java\n2. UserRepositoryPanache.java\n3. TagRepositoryPanache.java\n4. TagRelationshipRepositoryPanache.java\n5. FollowRelationshipRepositoryPanache.java\n6. FavoriteRelationshipRepositoryPanache.java\n7. CommentRepositoryPanache.java\n\nThe AbstractPanacheRepository used to have `@Inject protected EntityManager em;` but now has `protected EntityManager getEm()` method instead. The `em` field no longer exists.\n\nFor each of these 7 files:\n1. Read the file\n2. If the file has `@Inject private EntityManager em;` or `@jakarta.inject.Inject private EntityManager em;` or any form of injected `em` field, REMOVE that line entirely\n3. Replace ALL occurrences of `em.` (where `em` is used as a variable accessing the EntityManager) with `getEm().` - but ONLY when `em` refers to the EntityManager field. Do NOT replace things like `em` within other words (like \"name\", \"item\", etc). Specifically replace patterns like:\n   - `em.createQuery` → `getEm().createQuery`\n   - `em.persist` → `getEm().persist`\n   - `em.merge` → `getEm().merge`\n   - `em.find` → `getEm().find`\n   - `em.remove` → `getEm().remove`\n   - `em.flush` → `getEm().flush`\n4. Remove the EntityManager import if no longer needed (it might still be needed as a type in method signatures)\n\nUse the Edit tool for each change. Make sure to read each file first before editing.","subagent_type":"general-purpose"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1910,"cache_read_input_tokens":127823,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1910,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":652},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4d21e41c-7b8c-412a-ac18-df8336bdf9ca","uuid":"3cf25db4-cc5d-4140-ab40-3cff271df145"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"In the directory /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__realworld__quarkus__jakarta/run_1/output/src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/infrastructure/repository/hibernate/panache/, there are 7 repository files that extend AbstractPanacheRepository:\n\n1. ArticleRepositoryPanache.java\n2. UserRepositoryPanache.java\n3. TagRepositoryPanache.java\n4. TagRelationshipRepositoryPanache.java\n5. FollowRelationshipRepositoryPanache.java\n6. FavoriteRelationshipRepositoryPanache.java\n7. CommentRepositoryPanache.java\n\nThe AbstractPanacheRepository used to have `@Inject protected EntityManager em;` but now has `protected EntityManager getEm()` method instead. The `em` field no longer exists.\n\nFor each of these 7 files:\n1. Read the file\n2. If the file has `@Inject private EntityManager em;` or `@jakarta.inject.Inject private EntityManager em;` or any form of injected `em` field, REMOVE that line entirely\n3. Replace ALL occurrences of `em.` (where `em` is used as a variable accessing the EntityManager) with `getEm().` - but ONLY when `em` refers to the EntityManager field. Do NOT replace things like `em` within other words (like \"name\", \"item\", etc). Specifically replace patterns like:\n   - `em.createQuery` → `getEm().createQuery`\n   - `em.persist` → `getEm().persist`\n   - `em.merge` → `getEm().merge`\n   - `em.find` → `getEm().find`\n   - `em.remove` → `getEm().remove`\n   - `em.flush` → `getEm().flush`\n4. Remove the EntityManager import if no longer needed (it might still be needed as a type in method signatures)\n\nUse the Edit tool for each change. Make sure to read each file first before editing."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01PvTmr5gUZX2xBWznHGjRJ5","session_id":"4d21e41c-7b8c-412a-ac18-df8336bdf9ca","uuid":"8eb31ab2-c309-40fa-bfa1-2c5e5ae906d7"}
