{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01MjJBUUbBPG2s8FcMXNpDYX","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.repository.hibernate.panache;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\n     4→import java.util.List;\n     5→import java.util.Optional;\n     6→import java.util.UUID;\n     7→import java.util.stream.Collectors;\n     8→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article.Article;\n     9→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.comment.Comment;\n    10→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.comment.CommentRepository;\n    11→import org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.repository.hibernate.entity.CommentEntity;\n    12→import org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.repository.hibernate.entity.EntityUtils;\n    13→\n    14→@ApplicationScoped\n    15→public class CommentRepositoryPanache extends AbstractPanacheRepository\n    16→    implements CommentRepository {\n    17→\n    18→  @jakarta.inject.Inject private EntityUtils entityUtils;\n    19→\n    20→  @Override\n    21→  public void save(Comment comment) {\n    22→    final var authorEntity = findUserEntityById(comment.getAuthor().getId());\n    23→    final var articleEntity = findArticleEntityById(comment.getArticle().getId());\n    24→    em.persist(new CommentEntity(authorEntity, articleEntity, comment));\n    25→  }\n    26→\n    27→  @Override\n    28→  public Optional<Comment> findByIdAndAuthor(UUID commentId, UUID authorId) {\n    29→    var results =\n    30→        em.createQuery(\n    31→                \"from CommentEntity where id = :commentId and author.id = :authorId\",\n    32→                CommentEntity.class)\n    33→            .setParameter(\"commentId\", commentId)\n    34→            .setParameter(\"authorId\", authorId)\n    35→            .getResultList();\n    36→    return results.stream().findFirst().map(entityUtils::comment);\n    37→  }\n    38→\n    39→  @Override\n    40→  public void delete(Comment comment) {\n    41→    final var commentEntity = findCommentEntityById(comment.getId());\n    42→    if (commentEntity != null) {\n    43→      em.remove(commentEntity);\n    44→    }\n    45→  }\n    46→\n    47→  @Override\n    48→  public List<Comment> findCommentsByArticle(Article article) {\n    49→    var commentsEntity =\n    50→        em.createQuery(\n    51→                \"from CommentEntity where article.id = :articleId\", CommentEntity.class)\n    52→            .setParameter(\"articleId\", article.getId())\n    53→            .getResultList();\n    54→    return commentsEntity.stream().map(entityUtils::comment).collect(Collectors.toList());\n    55→  }\n    56→}\n    57→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01PvTmr5gUZX2xBWznHGjRJ5","session_id":"4d21e41c-7b8c-412a-ac18-df8336bdf9ca","uuid":"9c40cdab-217b-4098-8ab7-c989762b0193"}
