{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01NaDedVt6iiajgMx1kcs876","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.repository.hibernate.panache;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\n     4→import java.util.List;\n     5→import java.util.Optional;\n     6→import java.util.UUID;\n     7→import java.util.stream.Collectors;\n     8→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article.Article;\n     9→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.comment.Comment;\n    10→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.comment.CommentRepository;\n    11→import org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.repository.hibernate.entity.CommentEntity;\n    12→import org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.repository.hibernate.entity.EntityUtils;\n    13→\n    14→@ApplicationScoped\n    15→public class CommentRepositoryPanache extends AbstractPanacheRepository\n    16→    implements CommentRepository {\n    17→\n    18→  @jakarta.inject.Inject private EntityUtils entityUtils;\n    19→\n    20→  @Override\n    21→  public void save(Comment comment) {\n    22→    final var authorEntity = findUserEntityById(comment.getAuthor().getId());\n    23→    final var articleEntity = findArticleEntityById(comment.getArticle().getId());\n    24→    getEm().persist(new CommentEntity(authorEntity, articleEntity, comment));\n    25→  }\n    26→\n    27→  @Override\n    28→  public Optional<Comment> findByIdAndAuthor(UUID commentId, UUID authorId) {\n    29→    var results =\n    30→        getEm().createQuery(\n    31→                \"from CommentEntity where id = :commentId and author.id = :authorId\",\n    32→                CommentEntity.class)\n    33→            .setParameter(\"commentId\", commentId)\n    34→            .setParameter(\"authorId\", authorId)\n    35→            .getResultList();\n    36→    return results.stream().findFirst().map(entityUtils::comment);\n    37→  }\n    38→\n    39→  @Override\n    40→  public void delete(Comment comment) {\n    41→    final var commentEntity = findCommentEntityById(comment.getId());\n    42→    if (commentEntity != null) {\n    43→      getEm().remove(commentEntity);\n    44→    }\n    45→  }\n    46→\n    47→  @Override\n    48→  public List<Comment> findCommentsByArticle(Article article) {\n    49→    var commentsEntity =\n    50→        getEm().createQuery(\n    51→                \"from CommentEntity where article.id = :articleId\", CommentEntity.class)\n    52→            .setParameter(\"articleId\", article.getId())\n    53→            .getResultList();\n    54→    return commentsEntity.stream().map(entityUtils::comment).collect(Collectors.toList());\n    55→  }\n    56→}\n    57→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01PvTmr5gUZX2xBWznHGjRJ5","session_id":"4d21e41c-7b8c-412a-ac18-df8336bdf9ca","uuid":"760d56e7-29be-4e97-8523-e1f4e28537d1"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01PvTmr5gUZX2xBWznHGjRJ5","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! All changes have been successfully completed. Let me provide a summary of the work done:\n\n## Summary\n\nI have successfully migrated all 7 repository files from using the direct `em` EntityManager field to using the `getEm()` method provided by the AbstractPanacheRepository class. Here's what was completed:\n\n### Files Updated:\n\n1. **ArticleRepositoryPanache.java** - Updated 11 occurrences of `em.` to `getEm().`\n   - Methods affected: existsBySlug, save, findArticleById, findBySlug, update, findByAuthorAndSlug, delete, findMostRecentArticlesByFilter, findArticlesByFilter, count, countByLoggedUser\n\n2. **UserRepositoryPanache.java** - Updated 8 occurrences of `em.` to `getEm().`\n   - Methods affected: save, existsBy, findByEmail, findUserById, existsUsername, existsEmail, update, findByUsername\n\n3. **TagRepositoryPanache.java** - Updated 4 occurrences of `em.` to `getEm().`\n   - Methods affected: findAllTags, findByName, save, findByNames\n\n4. **TagRelationshipRepositoryPanache.java** - Updated 2 occurrences of `em.` to `getEm().`\n   - Methods affected: save, findArticleTags\n\n5. **FollowRelationshipRepositoryPanache.java** - Updated 4 occurrences of `em.` to `getEm().`\n   - Methods affected: isFollowing, save, remove, findUsersFollowedEntityByUsers\n\n6. **FavoriteRelationshipRepositoryPanache.java** - Updated 5 occurrences of `em.` to `getEm().`\n   - Methods affected: isFavorited, favoritesCount, findByArticleIdAndUserId, save, delete\n\n7. **CommentRepositoryPanache.java** - Updated 4 occurrences of `em.` to `getEm().`\n   - Methods affected: save, findByIdAndAuthor, delete, findCommentsByArticle\n\n### Changes Made:\n\n- Replaced all instances of `em.createQuery` with `getEm().createQuery`\n- Replaced all instances of `em.persist` with `getEm().persist`\n- Replaced all instances of `em.merge` with `getEm().merge`\n- Replaced all instances of `em.find` with `getEm().find`\n- Replaced all instances of `em.remove` with `getEm().remove`\n- Replaced all instances of `em.flush` with `getEm().flush`\n\n### Notes:\n\n- None of the files had an explicit `@Inject private EntityManager em;` field declaration - they were all inheriting the `em` field from AbstractPanacheRepository\n- All EntityManager imports are still present and needed since EntityManager is still used as a type reference in the codebase\n- The migration is now complete and all repositories will use the `getEm()` method instead of the direct field access\n\nAll files have been successfully updated to work with the new AbstractPanacheRepository API that provides `getEm()` method instead of the injected `em` field."}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4d21e41c-7b8c-412a-ac18-df8336bdf9ca","uuid":"3bc09686-e804-4379-b501-25b1da6d61de"}
